2854 /*
2855  * Parse the address range, if any, in "eap".
2856  * May set the last search pattern, unless "silent" is TRUE.
2857  * Return FAIL and set "errormsg" or return OK.
2858  */
2859  int
2860 parse_cmd_address(exarg_T *eap, char **errormsg, int silent)
2861 {
2862  int address_count = 1;
2863  linenr_T lnum;
2864 
2865  // Repeat for all ',' or ';' separated addresses.
2866  for (;;)
2867  {
2868  eap->line1 = eap->line2;
2869  switch (eap->addr_type)
2870  {
2871  case ADDR_LINES:
2872  case ADDR_OTHER:
2873  // default is current line number
2874  eap->line2 = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
2875  break;
2876  case ADDR_WINDOWS:
2877  eap->line2 = CURRENT_WIN_NR;
2878  break;
2879  case ADDR_ARGUMENTS:
2880  eap->line2 = curwin->w_arg_idx + 1;
2881  if (eap->line2 > ARGCOUNT)
2882  eap->line2 = ARGCOUNT;
2883  break;
2884  case ADDR_LOADED_BUFFERS:
2885  case ADDR_BUFFERS:
2886  eap->line2 = curbuf->b_fnum;
2887  break;
2888  case ADDR_TABS:
2889  eap->line2 = CURRENT_TAB_NR;
2890  break;
2891  case ADDR_TABS_RELATIVE:
2892  case ADDR_UNSIGNED:
2893  eap->line2 = 1;
2894  break;
2895  case ADDR_QUICKFIX:
2896 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
2897  eap->line2 = qf_get_cur_idx(eap);
2898 #endif
2899  break;
2900  case ADDR_QUICKFIX_VALID:
2901 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
2902  eap->line2 = qf_get_cur_valid_idx(eap);
2903 #endif
2904  break;
2905  case ADDR_NONE:
2906  // Will give an error later if a range is found.
2907  break;
2908  }
2909  eap->cmd = skipwhite(eap->cmd);
2910  lnum = get_address(eap, &eap->cmd, eap->addr_type, eap->skip, silent,
2911  eap->addr_count == 0, address_count++);
2912  if (eap->cmd == NULL) // error detected
2913  return FAIL;
2914  if (lnum == MAXLNUM)
2915  {
2916  if (*eap->cmd == '%') // '%' - all lines
2917  {
2918  ++eap->cmd;
2919  switch (eap->addr_type)
2920  {
2921  case ADDR_LINES:
2922  case ADDR_OTHER:
2923  eap->line1 = 1;
2924  eap->line2 = curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count;
2925  break;
2926  case ADDR_LOADED_BUFFERS:
2927  {
2928  buf_T *buf = firstbuf;
2929 
2930  while (buf->b_next != NULL
2931  && buf->b_ml.ml_mfp == NULL)
2932  buf = buf->b_next;
2933  eap->line1 = buf->b_fnum;
2934  buf = lastbuf;
2935  while (buf->b_prev != NULL
2936  && buf->b_ml.ml_mfp == NULL)
2937  buf = buf->b_prev;
2938  eap->line2 = buf->b_fnum;
2939  break;
2940  }
2941  case ADDR_BUFFERS:
2942  eap->line1 = firstbuf->b_fnum;
2943  eap->line2 = lastbuf->b_fnum;
2944  break;
2945  case ADDR_WINDOWS:
2946  case ADDR_TABS:
2947  if (IS_USER_CMDIDX(eap->cmdidx))
2948  {
2949  eap->line1 = 1;
2950  eap->line2 = eap->addr_type == ADDR_WINDOWS
2951  ? LAST_WIN_NR : LAST_TAB_NR;
2952  }
2953  else
2954  {
2955  // there is no Vim command which uses '%' and
2956  // ADDR_WINDOWS or ADDR_TABS
2957  *errormsg = _(e_invrange);
2958  return FAIL;
2959  }
2960  break;
2961  case ADDR_TABS_RELATIVE:
2962  case ADDR_UNSIGNED:
2963  case ADDR_QUICKFIX:
2964  *errormsg = _(e_invrange);
2965  return FAIL;
2966  case ADDR_ARGUMENTS:
2967  if (ARGCOUNT == 0)
2968  eap->line1 = eap->line2 = 0;
2969  else
2970  {
2971  eap->line1 = 1;
2972  eap->line2 = ARGCOUNT;
2973  }
2974  break;
2975  case ADDR_QUICKFIX_VALID:
2976 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
2977  eap->line1 = 1;
2978  eap->line2 = qf_get_valid_size(eap);
2979  if (eap->line2 == 0)
2980  eap->line2 = 1;
2981 #endif
2982  break;
2983  case ADDR_NONE:
2984  // Will give an error later if a range is found.
2985  break;
2986  }
2987  ++eap->addr_count;
2988  }
2989  else if (*eap->cmd == '*' && vim_strchr(p_cpo, CPO_STAR) == NULL)
2990  {
2991  pos_T *fp;
2992 
2993  // '*' - visual area
2994  if (eap->addr_type != ADDR_LINES)
2995  {
2996  *errormsg = _(e_invrange);
2997  return FAIL;
2998  }
2999 
3000  ++eap->cmd;
3001  if (!eap->skip)
3002  {
3003  fp = getmark('<', FALSE);
3004  if (check_mark(fp) == FAIL)
3005  return FAIL;
3006  eap->line1 = fp->lnum;
3007  fp = getmark('>', FALSE);
3008  if (check_mark(fp) == FAIL)
3009  return FAIL;
3010  eap->line2 = fp->lnum;
3011  ++eap->addr_count;
3012  }
3013  }
3014  }
3015  else
3016  eap->line2 = lnum;
3017  eap->addr_count++;
3018 
3019  if (*eap->cmd == ';')
3020  {
3021  if (!eap->skip)
3022  {
3023  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line2;
3024  // don't leave the cursor on an illegal line or column
3025  check_cursor();
3026  }
3027  }
3028  else if (*eap->cmd != ',')
3029  break;
3030  ++eap->cmd;
3031  }
3032 
3033  // One address given: set start and end lines.
3034  if (eap->addr_count == 1)
3035  {
3036  eap->line1 = eap->line2;
3037  // ... but only implicit: really no address given
3038  if (lnum == MAXLNUM)
3039  eap->addr_count = 0;
3040  }
3041  return OK;
3042 }
3043 
3044 /*
3045  * Check for an Ex command with optional tail.
3046  * If there is a match advance "pp" to the argument and return TRUE.
3047  */
3048  int
3049 checkforcmd(
3050  char_u **pp, /* start of command */
3051  char *cmd, /* name of command */
3052  int len) /* required length */
3053 {
3054  int i;
3055 
3056  for (i = 0; cmd[i] != NUL; ++i)
3057  if (((char_u *)cmd)[i] != (*pp)[i])
3058  break;
3059  if (i >= len && !isalpha((*pp)[i]))
3060  {
3061  *pp = skipwhite(*pp + i);
3062  return TRUE;
3063  }
3064  return FALSE;
3065 }
3066 
3067 /*
3068  * Append "cmd" to the error message in IObuff.
3069  * Takes care of limiting the length and handling 0xa0, which would be
3070  * invisible otherwise.
3071  */
3072  static void
3073 append_command(char_u *cmd)
3074 {
3075  char_u *s = cmd;
3076  char_u *d;
3077 
3078  STRCAT(IObuff, ": ");
3079  d = IObuff + STRLEN(IObuff);
3080  while (*s != NUL && d - IObuff < IOSIZE - 7)
3081  {
3082  if (enc_utf8 ? (s[0] == 0xc2 && s[1] == 0xa0) : *s == 0xa0)
3083  {
3084  s += enc_utf8 ? 2 : 1;
3085  STRCPY(d, "<a0>");
3086  d += 4;
3087  }
3088  else
3089  MB_COPY_CHAR(s, d);
3090  }
3091  *d = NUL;
3092 }
3093 
3094 /*
3095  * Find an Ex command by its name, either built-in or user.
3096  * Start of the name can be found at eap->cmd.
3097  * Sets eap->cmdidx and returns a pointer to char after the command name.
3098  * "full" is set to TRUE if the whole command name matched.
3099  * Returns NULL for an ambiguous user command.
3100  */
3101  static char_u *
3102 find_command(exarg_T *eap, int *full UNUSED)
3103 {
3104  int len;
3105  char_u *p;
3106  int i;
3107 
3108  /*
3109  * Isolate the command and search for it in the command table.
3110  * Exceptions:
3111  * - the 'k' command can directly be followed by any character.
3112  * - the 's' command can be followed directly by 'c', 'g', 'i', 'I' or 'r'
3113  * but :sre[wind] is another command, as are :scr[iptnames],
3114  * :scs[cope], :sim[alt], :sig[ns] and :sil[ent].
3115  * - the "d" command can directly be followed by 'l' or 'p' flag.
3116  */
3117  p = eap->cmd;
3118  if (*p == 'k')
3119  {
3120  eap->cmdidx = CMD_k;
3121  ++p;
3122  }
3123  else if (p[0] == 's'
3124  && ((p[1] == 'c' && (p[2] == NUL || (p[2] != 's' && p[2] != 'r'
3125  && (p[3] == NUL || (p[3] != 'i' && p[4] != 'p')))))
3126  || p[1] == 'g'
3127  || (p[1] == 'i' && p[2] != 'm' && p[2] != 'l' && p[2] != 'g')
3128  || p[1] == 'I'
3129  || (p[1] == 'r' && p[2] != 'e')))
3130  {
3131  eap->cmdidx = CMD_substitute;
3132  ++p;
3133  }
3134  else
3135  {
3136  while (ASCII_ISALPHA(*p))
3137  ++p;
3138  /* for python 3.x support ":py3", ":python3", ":py3file", etc. */
3139  if (eap->cmd[0] == 'p' && eap->cmd[1] == 'y')
3140  while (ASCII_ISALNUM(*p))
3141  ++p;
3142 
3143  /* check for non-alpha command */
3144  if (p == eap->cmd && vim_strchr((char_u *)"@*!=><&~#", *p) != NULL)
3145  ++p;
3146  len = (int)(p - eap->cmd);
3147  if (*eap->cmd == 'd' && (p[-1] == 'l' || p[-1] == 'p'))
3148  {
3149  /* Check for ":dl", ":dell", etc. to ":deletel": that's
3150  * :delete with the 'l' flag. Same for 'p'. */
3151  for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
3152  if (eap->cmd[i] != ((char_u *)"delete")[i])
3153  break;
3154  if (i == len - 1)
3155  {
3156  --len;
3157  if (p[-1] == 'l')
3158  eap->flags |= EXFLAG_LIST;
3159  else
3160  eap->flags |= EXFLAG_PRINT;
3161  }
3162  }
3163 
3164  if (ASCII_ISLOWER(eap->cmd[0]))
3165  {
3166  int c1 = eap->cmd[0];
3167  int c2 = len == 1 ? NUL : eap->cmd[1];
3168 
3169  if (command_count != (int)CMD_SIZE)
3170  {
3171  iemsg(_("E943: Command table needs to be updated, run 'make cmdidxs'"));
3172  getout(1);
3173  }
3174 
3175  /* Use a precomputed index for fast look-up in cmdnames[]
3176  * taking into account the first 2 letters of eap->cmd. */
3177  eap->cmdidx = cmdidxs1[CharOrdLow(c1)];
3178  if (ASCII_ISLOWER(c2))
3179  eap->cmdidx += cmdidxs2[CharOrdLow(c1)][CharOrdLow(c2)];
3180  }
3181  else
3182  eap->cmdidx = CMD_bang;
3183 
3184  for ( ; (int)eap->cmdidx < (int)CMD_SIZE;
3185  eap->cmdidx = (cmdidx_T)((int)eap->cmdidx + 1))
3186  if (STRNCMP(cmdnames[(int)eap->cmdidx].cmd_name, (char *)eap->cmd,
3187  (size_t)len) == 0)
3188  {
3189 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
3190  if (full != NULL
3191  && cmdnames[(int)eap->cmdidx].cmd_name[len] == NUL)
3192  *full = TRUE;
3193 #endif
3194  break;
3195  }
3196 
3197  // Look for a user defined command as a last resort. Let ":Print" be
3198  // overruled by a user defined command.
3199  if ((eap->cmdidx == CMD_SIZE || eap->cmdidx == CMD_Print)
3200  && *eap->cmd >= 'A' && *eap->cmd <= 'Z')
3201  {
3202  // User defined commands may contain digits.
3203  while (ASCII_ISALNUM(*p))
3204  ++p;
3205  p = find_ucmd(eap, p, full, NULL, NULL);
3206  }
3207  if (p == eap->cmd)
3208  eap->cmdidx = CMD_SIZE;
3209  }
3210 
3211  return p;
3212 }
3213 
3214 #if defined(FEAT_EVAL) || defined(PROTO)
3215 static struct cmdmod
3216 {
3217  char *name;
3218  int minlen;
3219  int has_count; /* :123verbose :3tab */
3220 } cmdmods[] = {
3221  {"aboveleft", 3, FALSE},
3222  {"belowright", 3, FALSE},
3223  {"botright", 2, FALSE},
3224  {"browse", 3, FALSE},
3225  {"confirm", 4, FALSE},
3226  {"filter", 4, FALSE},
3227  {"hide", 3, FALSE},
3228  {"keepalt", 5, FALSE},
3229  {"keepjumps", 5, FALSE},
3230  {"keepmarks", 3, FALSE},
3231  {"keeppatterns", 5, FALSE},
3232  {"leftabove", 5, FALSE},
3233  {"lockmarks", 3, FALSE},
3234  {"noautocmd", 3, FALSE},
3235  {"noswapfile", 3, FALSE},
3236  {"rightbelow", 6, FALSE},
3237  {"sandbox", 3, FALSE},
3238  {"silent", 3, FALSE},
3239  {"tab", 3, TRUE},
3240  {"topleft", 2, FALSE},
3241  {"unsilent", 3, FALSE},
3242  {"verbose", 4, TRUE},
3243  {"vertical", 4, FALSE},
3244 };

3246 /*
3247  * Return length of a command modifier (including optional count).
3248  * Return zero when it's not a modifier.
3249  */
3250  int
3251 modifier_len(char_u *cmd)
3252 {
3253  int i, j;
3254  char_u *p = cmd;
3255 
3256  if (VIM_ISDIGIT(*cmd))
3257  p = skipwhite(skipdigits(cmd));
3258  for (i = 0; i < (int)(sizeof(cmdmods) / sizeof(struct cmdmod)); ++i)
3259  {
3260  for (j = 0; p[j] != NUL; ++j)
3261  if (p[j] != cmdmods[i].name[j])
3262  break;
3263  if (!ASCII_ISALPHA(p[j]) && j >= cmdmods[i].minlen
3264  && (p == cmd || cmdmods[i].has_count))
3265  return j + (int)(p - cmd);
3266  }
3267  return 0;
3268 }
3269 
3270 /*
3271  * Return > 0 if an Ex command "name" exists.
3272  * Return 2 if there is an exact match.
3273  * Return 3 if there is an ambiguous match.
3274  */
3275  int
3276 cmd_exists(char_u *name)
3277 {
3278  exarg_T ea;
3279  int full = FALSE;
3280  int i;
3281  int j;
3282  char_u *p;
3283 
3284  /* Check command modifiers. */
3285  for (i = 0; i < (int)(sizeof(cmdmods) / sizeof(struct cmdmod)); ++i)
3286  {
3287  for (j = 0; name[j] != NUL; ++j)
3288  if (name[j] != cmdmods[i].name[j])
3289  break;
3290  if (name[j] == NUL && j >= cmdmods[i].minlen)
3291  return (cmdmods[i].name[j] == NUL ? 2 : 1);
3292  }
3293 
3294  /* Check built-in commands and user defined commands.
3295  * For ":2match" and ":3match" we need to skip the number. */
3296  ea.cmd = (*name == '2' || *name == '3') ? name + 1 : name;
3297  ea.cmdidx = (cmdidx_T)0;
3298  p = find_command(&ea, &full);
3299  if (p == NULL)
3300  return 3;
3301  if (vim_isdigit(*name) && ea.cmdidx != CMD_match)
3302  return 0;
3303  if (*skipwhite(p) != NUL)
3304  return 0; /* trailing garbage */
3305  return (ea.cmdidx == CMD_SIZE ? 0 : (full ? 2 : 1));
3306 }
3307 #endif
3308 
3309  cmdidx_T
3310 excmd_get_cmdidx(char_u *cmd, int len)
3311 {
3312  cmdidx_T idx;
3313 
3314  for (idx = (cmdidx_T)0; (int)idx < (int)CMD_SIZE;
3315  idx = (cmdidx_T)((int)idx + 1))
3316  if (STRNCMP(cmdnames[(int)idx].cmd_name, cmd, (size_t)len) == 0)
3317  break;
3318 
3319  return idx;
3320 }
3321 
3322  long
3323 excmd_get_argt(cmdidx_T idx)
3324 {
3325  return (long)cmdnames[(int)idx].cmd_argt;
3326 }
3327 
3328 /*
3329  * Skip a range specifier of the form: addr [,addr] [;addr] ..
3330  *
3331  * Backslashed delimiters after / or ? will be skipped, and commands will
3332  * not be expanded between /'s and ?'s or after "'".
3333  *
3334  * Also skip white space and ":" characters.
3335  * Returns the "cmd" pointer advanced to beyond the range.
3336  */
3337  char_u *
3338 skip_range(
3339  char_u *cmd,
3340  int *ctx) /* pointer to xp_context or NULL */
3341 {
3342  unsigned delim;
3343 
3344  while (vim_strchr((char_u *)" \t0123456789.$%'/?-+,;\\", *cmd) != NULL)
3345  {
3346  if (*cmd == '\\')
3347  {
3348  if (cmd[1] == '?' || cmd[1] == '/' || cmd[1] == '&')
3349  ++cmd;
3350  else
3351  break;
3352  }
3353  else if (*cmd == '\'')
3354  {
3355  if (*++cmd == NUL && ctx != NULL)
3356  *ctx = EXPAND_NOTHING;
3357  }
3358  else if (*cmd == '/' || *cmd == '?')
3359  {
3360  delim = *cmd++;
3361  while (*cmd != NUL && *cmd != delim)
3362  if (*cmd++ == '\\' && *cmd != NUL)
3363  ++cmd;
3364  if (*cmd == NUL && ctx != NULL)
3365  *ctx = EXPAND_NOTHING;
3366  }
3367  if (*cmd != NUL)
3368  ++cmd;
3369  }
3370 
3371  /* Skip ":" and white space. */
3372  while (*cmd == ':')
3373  cmd = skipwhite(cmd + 1);
3374 
3375  return cmd;
3376 }
3377 
3378  static void
3379 addr_error(cmd_addr_T addr_type)
3380 {
3381  if (addr_type == ADDR_NONE)
3382  emsg(_(e_norange));
3383  else
3384  emsg(_(e_invrange));
3385 }
3386 
3387 /*
3388  * Get a single EX address.
3389  *
3390  * Set ptr to the next character after the part that was interpreted.
3391  * Set ptr to NULL when an error is encountered.
3392  * This may set the last used search pattern.
3393  *
3394  * Return MAXLNUM when no Ex address was found.
3395  */
3396  static linenr_T
3397 get_address(
3398  exarg_T *eap UNUSED,
3399  char_u **ptr,
3400  cmd_addr_T addr_type_arg,
3401  int skip, // only skip the address, don't use it
3402  int silent, // no errors or side effects
3403  int to_other_file, // flag: may jump to other file
3404  int address_count UNUSED) // 1 for first address, >1 after comma
3405 {
3406  cmd_addr_T addr_type = addr_type_arg;
3407  int c;
3408  int i;
3409  long n;
3410  char_u *cmd;
3411  pos_T pos;
3412  pos_T *fp;
3413  linenr_T lnum;
3414  buf_T *buf;
3415 
3416  cmd = skipwhite(*ptr);
3417  lnum = MAXLNUM;
3418  do
3419  {
3420  switch (*cmd)
3421  {
3422  case '.': /* '.' - Cursor position */
3423  ++cmd;
3424  switch (addr_type)
3425  {
3426  case ADDR_LINES:
3427  case ADDR_OTHER:
3428  lnum = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
3429  break;
3430  case ADDR_WINDOWS:
3431  lnum = CURRENT_WIN_NR;
3432  break;
3433  case ADDR_ARGUMENTS:
3434  lnum = curwin->w_arg_idx + 1;
3435  break;
3436  case ADDR_LOADED_BUFFERS:
3437  case ADDR_BUFFERS:
3438  lnum = curbuf->b_fnum;
3439  break;
3440  case ADDR_TABS:
3441  lnum = CURRENT_TAB_NR;
3442  break;
3443  case ADDR_NONE:
3444  case ADDR_TABS_RELATIVE:
3445  case ADDR_UNSIGNED:
3446  addr_error(addr_type);
3447  cmd = NULL;
3448  goto error;
3449  break;
3450  case ADDR_QUICKFIX:
3451 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3452  lnum = qf_get_cur_idx(eap);
3453 #endif
3454  break;
3455  case ADDR_QUICKFIX_VALID:
3456 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3457  lnum = qf_get_cur_valid_idx(eap);
3458 #endif
3459  break;
3460  }
3461  break;
3462 
3463  case '$': /* '$' - last line */
3464  ++cmd;
3465  switch (addr_type)
3466  {
3467  case ADDR_LINES:
3468  case ADDR_OTHER:
3469  lnum = curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count;
3470  break;
3471  case ADDR_WINDOWS:
3472  lnum = LAST_WIN_NR;
3473  break;
3474  case ADDR_ARGUMENTS:
3475  lnum = ARGCOUNT;
3476  break;
3477  case ADDR_LOADED_BUFFERS:
3478  buf = lastbuf;
3479  while (buf->b_ml.ml_mfp == NULL)
3480  {
3481  if (buf->b_prev == NULL)
3482  break;
3483  buf = buf->b_prev;
3484  }
3485  lnum = buf->b_fnum;
3486  break;
3487  case ADDR_BUFFERS:
3488  lnum = lastbuf->b_fnum;
3489  break;
3490  case ADDR_TABS:
3491  lnum = LAST_TAB_NR;
3492  break;
3493  case ADDR_NONE:
3494  case ADDR_TABS_RELATIVE:
3495  case ADDR_UNSIGNED:
3496  addr_error(addr_type);
3497  cmd = NULL;
3498  goto error;
3499  break;
3500  case ADDR_QUICKFIX:
3501 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3502  lnum = qf_get_size(eap);
3503  if (lnum == 0)
3504  lnum = 1;
3505 #endif
3506  break;
3507  case ADDR_QUICKFIX_VALID:
3508 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3509  lnum = qf_get_valid_size(eap);
3510  if (lnum == 0)
3511  lnum = 1;
3512 #endif
3513  break;
3514  }
3515  break;
3516 
3517  case '\'': /* ''' - mark */
3518  if (*++cmd == NUL)
3519  {
3520  cmd = NULL;
3521  goto error;
3522  }
3523  if (addr_type != ADDR_LINES)
3524  {
3525  addr_error(addr_type);
3526  cmd = NULL;
3527  goto error;
3528  }
3529  if (skip)
3530  ++cmd;
3531  else
3532  {
3533  /* Only accept a mark in another file when it is
3534  * used by itself: ":'M". */
3535  fp = getmark(*cmd, to_other_file && cmd[1] == NUL);
3536  ++cmd;
3537  if (fp == (pos_T *)-1)
3538  /* Jumped to another file. */
3539  lnum = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
3540  else
3541  {
3542  if (check_mark(fp) == FAIL)
3543  {
3544  cmd = NULL;
3545  goto error;
3546  }
3547  lnum = fp->lnum;
3548  }
3549  }
3550  break;
3551 
3552  case '/':
3553  case '?': /* '/' or '?' - search */
3554  c = *cmd++;
3555  if (addr_type != ADDR_LINES)
3556  {
3557  addr_error(addr_type);
3558  cmd = NULL;
3559  goto error;
3560  }
3561  if (skip) /* skip "/pat/" */
3562  {
3563  cmd = skip_regexp(cmd, c, (int)p_magic, NULL);
3564  if (*cmd == c)
3565  ++cmd;
3566  }
3567  else
3568  {
3569  int flags;
3570 
3571  pos = curwin->w_cursor; // save curwin->w_cursor
3572 
3573  // When '/' or '?' follows another address, start from
3574  // there.
3575  if (lnum != MAXLNUM)
3576  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = lnum;
3577 
3578  // Start a forward search at the end of the line (unless
3579  // before the first line).
3580  // Start a backward search at the start of the line.
3581  // This makes sure we never match in the current
3582  // line, and can match anywhere in the
3583  // next/previous line.
3584  if (c == '/' && curwin->w_cursor.lnum > 0)
3585  curwin->w_cursor.col = MAXCOL;
3586  else
3587  curwin->w_cursor.col = 0;
3588  searchcmdlen = 0;
3589  flags = silent ? 0 : SEARCH_HIS | SEARCH_MSG;
3590  if (!do_search(NULL, c, cmd, 1L, flags, NULL, NULL))
3591  {
3592  curwin->w_cursor = pos;
3593  cmd = NULL;
3594  goto error;
3595  }
3596  lnum = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
3597  curwin->w_cursor = pos;
3598  /* adjust command string pointer */
3599  cmd += searchcmdlen;
3600  }
3601  break;
3602 
3603  case '\\': /* "\?", "\/" or "\&", repeat search */
3604  ++cmd;
3605  if (addr_type != ADDR_LINES)
3606  {
3607  addr_error(addr_type);
3608  cmd = NULL;
3609  goto error;
3610  }
3611  if (*cmd == '&')
3612  i = RE_SUBST;
3613  else if (*cmd == '?' || *cmd == '/')
3614  i = RE_SEARCH;
3615  else
3616  {
3617  emsg(_(e_backslash));
3618  cmd = NULL;
3619  goto error;
3620  }
3621 
3622  if (!skip)
3623  {
3624  /*
3625  * When search follows another address, start from
3626  * there.
3627  */
3628  if (lnum != MAXLNUM)
3629  pos.lnum = lnum;
3630  else
3631  pos.lnum = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
3632 
3633  /*
3634  * Start the search just like for the above
3635  * do_search().
3636  */
3637  if (*cmd != '?')
3638  pos.col = MAXCOL;
3639  else
3640  pos.col = 0;
3641  pos.coladd = 0;
3642  if (searchit(curwin, curbuf, &pos, NULL,
3643  *cmd == '?' ? BACKWARD : FORWARD,
3644  (char_u *)"", 1L, SEARCH_MSG,
3645  i, (linenr_T)0, NULL, NULL) != FAIL)
3646  lnum = pos.lnum;
3647  else
3648  {
3649  cmd = NULL;
3650  goto error;
3651  }
3652  }
3653  ++cmd;
3654  break;
3655 
3656  default:
3657  if (VIM_ISDIGIT(*cmd)) /* absolute line number */
3658  lnum = getdigits(&cmd);
3659  }
3660 
3661  for (;;)
3662  {
3663  cmd = skipwhite(cmd);
3664  if (*cmd != '-' && *cmd != '+' && !VIM_ISDIGIT(*cmd))
3665  break;
3666 
3667  if (lnum == MAXLNUM)
3668  {
3669  switch (addr_type)
3670  {
3671  case ADDR_LINES:
3672  case ADDR_OTHER:
3673  // "+1" is same as ".+1"
3674  lnum = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
3675  break;
3676  case ADDR_WINDOWS:
3677  lnum = CURRENT_WIN_NR;
3678  break;
3679  case ADDR_ARGUMENTS:
3680  lnum = curwin->w_arg_idx + 1;
3681  break;
3682  case ADDR_LOADED_BUFFERS:
3683  case ADDR_BUFFERS:
3684  lnum = curbuf->b_fnum;
3685  break;
3686  case ADDR_TABS:
3687  lnum = CURRENT_TAB_NR;
3688  break;
3689  case ADDR_TABS_RELATIVE:
3690  lnum = 1;
3691  break;
3692  case ADDR_QUICKFIX:
3693 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3694  lnum = qf_get_cur_idx(eap);
3695 #endif
3696  break;
3697  case ADDR_QUICKFIX_VALID:
3698 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3699  lnum = qf_get_cur_valid_idx(eap);
3700 #endif
3701  break;
3702  case ADDR_NONE:
3703  case ADDR_UNSIGNED:
3704  lnum = 0;
3705  break;
3706  }
3707  }
3708 
3709  if (VIM_ISDIGIT(*cmd))
3710  i = '+'; /* "number" is same as "+number" */
3711  else
3712  i = *cmd++;
3713  if (!VIM_ISDIGIT(*cmd)) /* '+' is '+1', but '+0' is not '+1' */
3714  n = 1;
3715  else
3716  n = getdigits(&cmd);
3717 
3718  if (addr_type == ADDR_TABS_RELATIVE)
3719  {
3720  emsg(_(e_invrange));
3721  cmd = NULL;
3722  goto error;
3723  }
3724  else if (addr_type == ADDR_LOADED_BUFFERS
3725  || addr_type == ADDR_BUFFERS)
3726  lnum = compute_buffer_local_count(
3727  addr_type, lnum, (i == '-') ? -1 * n : n);
3728  else
3729  {
3730 #ifdef FEAT_FOLDING
3731  /* Relative line addressing, need to adjust for folded lines
3732  * now, but only do it after the first address. */
3733  if (addr_type == ADDR_LINES && (i == '-' || i == '+')
3734  && address_count >= 2)
3735  (void)hasFolding(lnum, NULL, &lnum);
3736 #endif
3737  if (i == '-')
3738  lnum -= n;
3739  else
3740  lnum += n;
3741  }
3742  }
3743  } while (*cmd == '/' || *cmd == '?');
3744 
3745 error:
3746  *ptr = cmd;
3747  return lnum;
3748 }
3749 
3750 /*
3751  * Get flags from an Ex command argument.
3752  */
3753  static void
3754 get_flags(exarg_T *eap)
3755 {
3756  while (vim_strchr((char_u *)"lp#", *eap->arg) != NULL)
3757  {
3758  if (*eap->arg == 'l')
3759  eap->flags |= EXFLAG_LIST;
3760  else if (*eap->arg == 'p')
3761  eap->flags |= EXFLAG_PRINT;
3762  else
3763  eap->flags |= EXFLAG_NR;
3764  eap->arg = skipwhite(eap->arg + 1);
3765  }
3766 }

3769  * Function called for command which is Not Implemented. NI!
3770  */
3771  void
3772 ex_ni(exarg_T *eap)
3773 {
3774  if (!eap->skip)
3775  eap->errmsg = N_("E319: Sorry, the command is not available in this version");
3776 }
3777 
3778 #ifdef HAVE_EX_SCRIPT_NI
3779 /*
3780  * Function called for script command which is Not Implemented. NI!
3781  * Skips over ":perl <<EOF" constructs.
3782  */
3783  static void
3784 ex_script_ni(exarg_T *eap)
3785 {
3786  if (!eap->skip)
3787  ex_ni(eap);
3788  else
3789  vim_free(script_get(eap, eap->arg));
3790 }

3793 /*
3794  * Check range in Ex command for validity.
3795  * Return NULL when valid, error message when invalid.
3796  */
3797  static char *
3798 invalid_range(exarg_T *eap)
3799 {
3800  buf_T *buf;
3801 
3802  if ( eap->line1 < 0
3803  || eap->line2 < 0
3804  || eap->line1 > eap->line2)
3805  return _(e_invrange);
3806 
3807  if (eap->argt & EX_RANGE)
3808  {
3809  switch (eap->addr_type)
3810  {
3811  case ADDR_LINES:
3812  if (eap->line2 > curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count
3813 #ifdef FEAT_DIFF
3814  + (eap->cmdidx == CMD_diffget)
3815 #endif
3816  )
3817  return _(e_invrange);
3818  break;
3819  case ADDR_ARGUMENTS:
3820  /* add 1 if ARGCOUNT is 0 */
3821  if (eap->line2 > ARGCOUNT + (!ARGCOUNT))
3822  return _(e_invrange);
3823  break;
3824  case ADDR_BUFFERS:
3825  // Only a boundary check, not whether the buffers actually
3826  // exist.
3827  if (eap->line1 < 1 || eap->line2 > get_highest_fnum())
3828  return _(e_invrange);
3829  break;
3830  case ADDR_LOADED_BUFFERS:
3831  buf = firstbuf;
3832  while (buf->b_ml.ml_mfp == NULL)
3833  {
3834  if (buf->b_next == NULL)
3835  return _(e_invrange);
3836  buf = buf->b_next;
3837  }
3838  if (eap->line1 < buf->b_fnum)
3839  return _(e_invrange);
3840  buf = lastbuf;
3841  while (buf->b_ml.ml_mfp == NULL)
3842  {
3843  if (buf->b_prev == NULL)
3844  return _(e_invrange);
3845  buf = buf->b_prev;
3846  }
3847  if (eap->line2 > buf->b_fnum)
3848  return _(e_invrange);
3849  break;
3850  case ADDR_WINDOWS:
3851  if (eap->line2 > LAST_WIN_NR)
3852  return _(e_invrange);
3853  break;
3854  case ADDR_TABS:
3855  if (eap->line2 > LAST_TAB_NR)
3856  return _(e_invrange);
3857  break;
3858  case ADDR_TABS_RELATIVE:
3859  case ADDR_OTHER:
3860  // Any range is OK.
3861  break;
3862  case ADDR_QUICKFIX:
3863 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3864  // No error for value that is too big, will use the last entry.
3865  if (eap->line2 <= 0)
3866  return _(e_invrange);
3867 #endif
3868  break;
3869  case ADDR_QUICKFIX_VALID:
3870 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3871  if ((eap->line2 != 1 && eap->line2 > qf_get_valid_size(eap))
3872  || eap->line2 < 0)
3873  return _(e_invrange);
3874 #endif
3875  break;
3876  case ADDR_UNSIGNED:
3877  if (eap->line2 < 0)
3878  return _(e_invrange);
3879  break;
3880  case ADDR_NONE:
3881  // Will give an error elsewhere.
3882  break;
3883  }
3884  }
3885  return NULL;
3886 }
3887 
3888 /*
3889  * Correct the range for zero line number, if required.
3890  */
3891  static void
3892 correct_range(exarg_T *eap)
3893 {
3894  if (!(eap->argt & EX_ZEROR)) // zero in range not allowed
3895  {
3896  if (eap->line1 == 0)
3897  eap->line1 = 1;
3898  if (eap->line2 == 0)
3899  eap->line2 = 1;
3900  }
3901 }

3903 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
3904 /*
3905  * For a ":vimgrep" or ":vimgrepadd" command return a pointer past the
3906  * pattern. Otherwise return eap->arg.
3907  */
3908  static char_u *
3909 skip_grep_pat(exarg_T *eap)
3910 {
3911  char_u *p = eap->arg;
3912 
3913  if (*p != NUL && (eap->cmdidx == CMD_vimgrep || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lvimgrep
3914  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_vimgrepadd
3915  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lvimgrepadd
3916  || grep_internal(eap->cmdidx)))
3917  {
3918  p = skip_vimgrep_pat(p, NULL, NULL);
3919  if (p == NULL)
3920  p = eap->arg;
3921  }
3922  return p;
3923 }

3925 /*
3926  * For the ":make" and ":grep" commands insert the 'makeprg'/'grepprg' option
3927  * in the command line, so that things like % get expanded.
3928  */
3929  static char_u *
3930 replace_makeprg(exarg_T *eap, char_u *p, char_u **cmdlinep)
3931 {
3932  char_u *new_cmdline;
3933  char_u *program;
3934  char_u *pos;
3935  char_u *ptr;
3936  int len;
3937  int i;
3938 
3939  /*
3940  * Don't do it when ":vimgrep" is used for ":grep".
3941  */
3942  if ((eap->cmdidx == CMD_make || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lmake
3943  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_grep || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lgrep
3944  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_grepadd
3945  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lgrepadd)
3946  && !grep_internal(eap->cmdidx))
3947  {
3948  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_grep || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lgrep
3949  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_grepadd || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lgrepadd)
3950  {
3951  if (*curbuf->b_p_gp == NUL)
3952  program = p_gp;
3953  else
3954  program = curbuf->b_p_gp;
3955  }
3956  else
3957  {
3958  if (*curbuf->b_p_mp == NUL)
3959  program = p_mp;
3960  else
3961  program = curbuf->b_p_mp;
3962  }
3963 
3964  p = skipwhite(p);
3965 
3966  if ((pos = (char_u *)strstr((char *)program, "$*")) != NULL)
3967  {
3968  /* replace $* by given arguments */
3969  i = 1;
3970  while ((pos = (char_u *)strstr((char *)pos + 2, "$*")) != NULL)
3971  ++i;
3972  len = (int)STRLEN(p);
3973  new_cmdline = alloc(STRLEN(program) + i * (len - 2) + 1);
3974  if (new_cmdline == NULL)
3975  return NULL; /* out of memory */
3976  ptr = new_cmdline;
3977  while ((pos = (char_u *)strstr((char *)program, "$*")) != NULL)
3978  {
3979  i = (int)(pos - program);
3980  STRNCPY(ptr, program, i);
3981  STRCPY(ptr += i, p);
3982  ptr += len;
3983  program = pos + 2;
3984  }
3985  STRCPY(ptr, program);
3986  }
3987  else
3988  {
3989  new_cmdline = alloc(STRLEN(program) + STRLEN(p) + 2);
3990  if (new_cmdline == NULL)
3991  return NULL; /* out of memory */
3992  STRCPY(new_cmdline, program);
3993  STRCAT(new_cmdline, " ");
3994  STRCAT(new_cmdline, p);
3995  }
3996  msg_make(p);
3997 
3998  /* 'eap->cmd' is not set here, because it is not used at CMD_make */
3999  vim_free(*cmdlinep);
4000  *cmdlinep = new_cmdline;
4001  p = new_cmdline;
4002  }
4003  return p;
4004 }
4005 #endif
4006 
4007 /*
4008  * Expand file name in Ex command argument.
4009  * When an error is detected, "errormsgp" is set to a non-NULL pointer.
4010  * Return FAIL for failure, OK otherwise.
4011  */
4012  int
4013 expand_filename(
4014  exarg_T *eap,
4015  char_u **cmdlinep,
4016  char **errormsgp)
4017 {
4018  int has_wildcards; /* need to expand wildcards */
4019  char_u *repl;
4020  int srclen;
4021  char_u *p;
4022  int n;
4023  int escaped;
4024 
4025 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
4026  /* Skip a regexp pattern for ":vimgrep[add] pat file..." */
4027  p = skip_grep_pat(eap);
4028 #else
4029  p = eap->arg;
4030 #endif
4031 
4032  /*
4033  * Decide to expand wildcards *before* replacing '%', '#', etc. If
4034  * the file name contains a wildcard it should not cause expanding.
4035  * (it will be expanded anyway if there is a wildcard before replacing).
4036  */
4037  has_wildcards = mch_has_wildcard(p);
4038  while (*p != NUL)
4039  {
4040 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
4041  /* Skip over `=expr`, wildcards in it are not expanded. */
4042  if (p[0] == '`' && p[1] == '=')
4043  {
4044  p += 2;
4045  (void)skip_expr(&p);
4046  if (*p == '`')
4047  ++p;
4048  continue;
4049  }
4050 #endif
4051  /*
4052  * Quick check if this cannot be the start of a special string.
4053  * Also removes backslash before '%', '#' and '<'.
4054  */
4055  if (vim_strchr((char_u *)"%#<", *p) == NULL)
4056  {
4057  ++p;
4058  continue;
4059  }
4060 
4061  /*
4062  * Try to find a match at this position.
4063  */
4064  repl = eval_vars(p, eap->arg, &srclen, &(eap->do_ecmd_lnum),
4065  errormsgp, &escaped);
4066  if (*errormsgp != NULL) /* error detected */
4067  return FAIL;
4068  if (repl == NULL) /* no match found */
4069  {
4070  p += srclen;
4071  continue;
4072  }
4073 
4074  /* Wildcards won't be expanded below, the replacement is taken
4075  * literally. But do expand "~/file", "~user/file" and "$HOME/file". */
4076  if (vim_strchr(repl, '$') != NULL || vim_strchr(repl, '~') != NULL)
4077  {
4078  char_u *l = repl;
4079 
4080  repl = expand_env_save(repl);
4081  vim_free(l);
4082  }
4083 
4084  /* Need to escape white space et al. with a backslash.
4085  * Don't do this for:
4086  * - replacement that already has been escaped: "##"
4087  * - shell commands (may have to use quotes instead).
4088  * - non-unix systems when there is a single argument (spaces don't
4089  * separate arguments then).
4090  */
4091  if (!eap->usefilter
4092  && !escaped
4093  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_bang
4094  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_grep
4095  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_grepadd
4096  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_hardcopy
4097  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_lgrep
4098  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_lgrepadd
4099  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_lmake
4100  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_make
4101  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_terminal
4102 #ifndef UNIX
4103  && !(eap->argt & EX_NOSPC)
4104 #endif
4105  )
4106  {
4107  char_u *l;
4108 #ifdef BACKSLASH_IN_FILENAME
4109  /* Don't escape a backslash here, because rem_backslash() doesn't
4110  * remove it later. */
4111  static char_u *nobslash = (char_u *)" \t\"|";
4112 # define ESCAPE_CHARS nobslash
4113 #else
4114 # define ESCAPE_CHARS escape_chars
4115 #endif
4116 
4117  for (l = repl; *l; ++l)
4118  if (vim_strchr(ESCAPE_CHARS, *l) != NULL)
4119  {
4120  l = vim_strsave_escaped(repl, ESCAPE_CHARS);
4121  if (l != NULL)
4122  {
4123  vim_free(repl);
4124  repl = l;
4125  }
4126  break;
4127  }
4128  }
4129 
4130  /* For a shell command a '!' must be escaped. */
4131  if ((eap->usefilter || eap->cmdidx == CMD_bang
4132  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_terminal)
4133  && vim_strpbrk(repl, (char_u *)"!") != NULL)
4134  {
4135  char_u *l;
4136 
4137  l = vim_strsave_escaped(repl, (char_u *)"!");
4138  if (l != NULL)
4139  {
4140  vim_free(repl);
4141  repl = l;
4142  }
4143  }
4144 
4145  p = repl_cmdline(eap, p, srclen, repl, cmdlinep);
4146  vim_free(repl);
4147  if (p == NULL)
4148  return FAIL;
4149  }
4150 
4151  /*
4152  * One file argument: Expand wildcards.
4153  * Don't do this with ":r !command" or ":w !command".
4154  */
4155  if ((eap->argt & EX_NOSPC) && !eap->usefilter)
4156  {
4157  /*
4158  * May do this twice:
4159  * 1. Replace environment variables.
4160  * 2. Replace any other wildcards, remove backslashes.
4161  */
4162  for (n = 1; n <= 2; ++n)
4163  {
4164  if (n == 2)
4165  {
4166  /*
4167  * Halve the number of backslashes (this is Vi compatible).
4168  * For Unix and OS/2, when wildcards are expanded, this is
4169  * done by ExpandOne() below.
4170  */
4171 #if defined(UNIX)
4172  if (!has_wildcards)
4173 #endif
4174  backslash_halve(eap->arg);
4175  }
4176 
4177  if (has_wildcards)
4178  {
4179  if (n == 1)
4180  {
4181  /*
4182  * First loop: May expand environment variables. This
4183  * can be done much faster with expand_env() than with
4184  * something else (e.g., calling a shell).
4185  * After expanding environment variables, check again
4186  * if there are still wildcards present.
4187  */
4188  if (vim_strchr(eap->arg, '$') != NULL
4189  || vim_strchr(eap->arg, '~') != NULL)
4190  {
4191  expand_env_esc(eap->arg, NameBuff, MAXPATHL,
4192  TRUE, TRUE, NULL);
4193  has_wildcards = mch_has_wildcard(NameBuff);
4194  p = NameBuff;
4195  }
4196  else
4197  p = NULL;
4198  }
4199  else /* n == 2 */
4200  {
4201  expand_T xpc;
4202  int options = WILD_LIST_NOTFOUND|WILD_ADD_SLASH;
4203 
4204  ExpandInit(&xpc);
4205  xpc.xp_context = EXPAND_FILES;
4206  if (p_wic)
4207  options += WILD_ICASE;
4208  p = ExpandOne(&xpc, eap->arg, NULL,
4209  options, WILD_EXPAND_FREE);
4210  if (p == NULL)
4211  return FAIL;
4212  }
4213  if (p != NULL)
4214  {
4215  (void)repl_cmdline(eap, eap->arg, (int)STRLEN(eap->arg),
4216  p, cmdlinep);
4217  if (n == 2) /* p came from ExpandOne() */
4218  vim_free(p);
4219  }
4220  }
4221  }
4222  }
4223  return OK;
4224 }
4225 
4226 /*
4227  * Replace part of the command line, keeping eap->cmd, eap->arg and
4228  * eap->nextcmd correct.
4229  * "src" points to the part that is to be replaced, of length "srclen".
4230  * "repl" is the replacement string.
4231  * Returns a pointer to the character after the replaced string.
4232  * Returns NULL for failure.
4233  */
4234  static char_u *
4235 repl_cmdline(
4236  exarg_T *eap,
4237  char_u *src,
4238  int srclen,
4239  char_u *repl,
4240  char_u **cmdlinep)
4241 {
4242  int len;
4243  int i;
4244  char_u *new_cmdline;
4245 
4246  /*
4247  * The new command line is build in new_cmdline[].
4248  * First allocate it.
4249  * Careful: a "+cmd" argument may have been NUL terminated.
4250  */
4251  len = (int)STRLEN(repl);
4252  i = (int)(src - *cmdlinep) + (int)STRLEN(src + srclen) + len + 3;
4253  if (eap->nextcmd != NULL)
4254  i += (int)STRLEN(eap->nextcmd);/* add space for next command */
4255  if ((new_cmdline = alloc(i)) == NULL)
4256  return NULL; /* out of memory! */
4257 
4258  /*
4259  * Copy the stuff before the expanded part.
4260  * Copy the expanded stuff.
4261  * Copy what came after the expanded part.
4262  * Copy the next commands, if there are any.
4263  */
4264  i = (int)(src - *cmdlinep); /* length of part before match */
4265  mch_memmove(new_cmdline, *cmdlinep, (size_t)i);
4266 
4267  mch_memmove(new_cmdline + i, repl, (size_t)len);
4268  i += len; /* remember the end of the string */
4269  STRCPY(new_cmdline + i, src + srclen);
4270  src = new_cmdline + i; /* remember where to continue */
4271 
4272  if (eap->nextcmd != NULL) /* append next command */
4273  {
4274  i = (int)STRLEN(new_cmdline) + 1;
4275  STRCPY(new_cmdline + i, eap->nextcmd);
4276  eap->nextcmd = new_cmdline + i;
4277  }
4278  eap->cmd = new_cmdline + (eap->cmd - *cmdlinep);
4279  eap->arg = new_cmdline + (eap->arg - *cmdlinep);
4280  if (eap->do_ecmd_cmd != NULL && eap->do_ecmd_cmd != dollar_command)
4281  eap->do_ecmd_cmd = new_cmdline + (eap->do_ecmd_cmd - *cmdlinep);
4282  vim_free(*cmdlinep);
4283  *cmdlinep = new_cmdline;
4284 
4285  return src;
4286 }
4287 
4288 /*
4289  * Check for '|' to separate commands and '"' to start comments.
4290  */
4291  void
4292 separate_nextcmd(exarg_T *eap)
4293 {
4294  char_u *p;
4295 
4296 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
4297  p = skip_grep_pat(eap);
4298 #else
4299  p = eap->arg;
4300 #endif
4301 
4302  for ( ; *p; MB_PTR_ADV(p))
4303  {
4304  if (*p == Ctrl_V)
4305  {
4306  if (eap->argt & (EX_CTRLV | EX_XFILE))
4307  ++p; /* skip CTRL-V and next char */
4308  else
4309  /* remove CTRL-V and skip next char */
4310  STRMOVE(p, p + 1);
4311  if (*p == NUL) /* stop at NUL after CTRL-V */
4312  break;
4313  }
4314 
4315 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
4316  /* Skip over `=expr` when wildcards are expanded. */
4317  else if (p[0] == '`' && p[1] == '=' && (eap->argt & EX_XFILE))
4318  {
4319  p += 2;
4320  (void)skip_expr(&p);
4321  }
4322 #endif
4323 
4324  /* Check for '"': start of comment or '|': next command */
4325  /* :@" and :*" do not start a comment!
4326  * :redir @" doesn't either. */
4327  else if ((*p == '"' && !(eap->argt & EX_NOTRLCOM)
4328  && ((eap->cmdidx != CMD_at && eap->cmdidx != CMD_star)
4329  || p != eap->arg)
4330  && (eap->cmdidx != CMD_redir
4331  || p != eap->arg + 1 || p[-1] != '@'))
4332  || *p == '|' || *p == '\n')
4333  {
4334  /*
4335  * We remove the '\' before the '|', unless EX_CTRLV is used
4336  * AND 'b' is present in 'cpoptions'.
4337  */
4338  if ((vim_strchr(p_cpo, CPO_BAR) == NULL
4339  || !(eap->argt & EX_CTRLV)) && *(p - 1) == '\\')
4340  {
4341  STRMOVE(p - 1, p); /* remove the '\' */
4342  --p;
4343  }
4344  else
4345  {
4346  eap->nextcmd = check_nextcmd(p);
4347  *p = NUL;
4348  break;
4349  }
4350  }
4351  }
4352 
4353  if (!(eap->argt & EX_NOTRLCOM)) /* remove trailing spaces */
4354  del_trailing_spaces(eap->arg);
4355 }
4356 
4357 /*
4358  * get + command from ex argument
4359  */
4360  static char_u *
4361 getargcmd(char_u **argp)
4362 {
4363  char_u *arg = *argp;
4364  char_u *command = NULL;
4365 
4366  if (*arg == '+') /* +[command] */
4367  {
4368  ++arg;
4369  if (vim_isspace(*arg) || *arg == NUL)
4370  command = dollar_command;
4371  else
4372  {
4373  command = arg;
4374  arg = skip_cmd_arg(command, TRUE);
4375  if (*arg != NUL)
4376  *arg++ = NUL; /* terminate command with NUL */
4377  }
4378 
4379  arg = skipwhite(arg); /* skip over spaces */
4380  *argp = arg;
4381  }
4382  return command;
4383 }
4384 
4385 /*
4386  * Find end of "+command" argument. Skip over "\ " and "\\".
4387  */
4388  char_u *
4389 skip_cmd_arg(
4390  char_u *p,
4391  int rembs) /* TRUE to halve the number of backslashes */
4392 {
4393  while (*p && !vim_isspace(*p))
4394  {
4395  if (*p == '\\' && p[1] != NUL)
4396  {
4397  if (rembs)
4398  STRMOVE(p, p + 1);
4399  else
4400  ++p;
4401  }
4402  MB_PTR_ADV(p);
4403  }
4404  return p;
4405 }
4406 
4407  int
4408 get_bad_opt(char_u *p, exarg_T *eap)
4409 {
4410  if (STRICMP(p, "keep") == 0)
4411  eap->bad_char = BAD_KEEP;
4412  else if (STRICMP(p, "drop") == 0)
4413  eap->bad_char = BAD_DROP;
4414  else if (MB_BYTE2LEN(*p) == 1 && p[1] == NUL)
4415  eap->bad_char = *p;
4416  else
4417  return FAIL;
4418  return OK;
4419 }
4420 
4421 /*
4422  * Get "++opt=arg" argument.
4423  * Return FAIL or OK.
4424  */
4425  static int
4426 getargopt(exarg_T *eap)
4427 {
4428  char_u *arg = eap->arg + 2;
4429  int *pp = NULL;
4430  int bad_char_idx;
4431  char_u *p;
4432 
4433  /* ":edit ++[no]bin[ary] file" */
4434  if (STRNCMP(arg, "bin", 3) == 0 || STRNCMP(arg, "nobin", 5) == 0)
4435  {
4436  if (*arg == 'n')
4437  {
4438  arg += 2;
4439  eap->force_bin = FORCE_NOBIN;
4440  }
4441  else
4442  eap->force_bin = FORCE_BIN;
4443  if (!checkforcmd(&arg, "binary", 3))
4444  return FAIL;
4445  eap->arg = skipwhite(arg);
4446  return OK;
4447  }
4448 
4449  /* ":read ++edit file" */
4450  if (STRNCMP(arg, "edit", 4) == 0)
4451  {
4452  eap->read_edit = TRUE;
4453  eap->arg = skipwhite(arg + 4);
4454  return OK;
4455  }
4456 
4457  if (STRNCMP(arg, "ff", 2) == 0)
4458  {
4459  arg += 2;
4460  pp = &eap->force_ff;
4461  }
4462  else if (STRNCMP(arg, "fileformat", 10) == 0)
4463  {
4464  arg += 10;
4465  pp = &eap->force_ff;
4466  }
4467  else if (STRNCMP(arg, "enc", 3) == 0)
4468  {
4469  if (STRNCMP(arg, "encoding", 8) == 0)
4470  arg += 8;
4471  else
4472  arg += 3;
4473  pp = &eap->force_enc;
4474  }
4475  else if (STRNCMP(arg, "bad", 3) == 0)
4476  {
4477  arg += 3;
4478  pp = &bad_char_idx;
4479  }
4480 
4481  if (pp == NULL || *arg != '=')
4482  return FAIL;
4483 
4484  ++arg;
4485  *pp = (int)(arg - eap->cmd);
4486  arg = skip_cmd_arg(arg, FALSE);
4487  eap->arg = skipwhite(arg);
4488  *arg = NUL;
4489 
4490  if (pp == &eap->force_ff)
4491  {
4492  if (check_ff_value(eap->cmd + eap->force_ff) == FAIL)
4493  return FAIL;
4494  eap->force_ff = eap->cmd[eap->force_ff];
4495  }
4496  else if (pp == &eap->force_enc)
4497  {
4498  /* Make 'fileencoding' lower case. */
4499  for (p = eap->cmd + eap->force_enc; *p != NUL; ++p)
4500  *p = TOLOWER_ASC(*p);
4501  }
4502  else
4503  {
4504  /* Check ++bad= argument. Must be a single-byte character, "keep" or
4505  * "drop". */
4506  if (get_bad_opt(eap->cmd + bad_char_idx, eap) == FAIL)
4507  return FAIL;
4508  }
4509 
4510  return OK;
4511 }
4512 
4513  static void
4514 ex_autocmd(exarg_T *eap)
4515 {
4516  /*
4517  * Disallow autocommands from .exrc and .vimrc in current
4518  * directory for security reasons.
4519  */
4520  if (secure)
4521  {
4522  secure = 2;
4523  eap->errmsg = e_curdir;
4524  }
4525  else if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_autocmd)
4526  do_autocmd(eap->arg, eap->forceit);
4527  else
4528  do_augroup(eap->arg, eap->forceit);
4529 }

4531 /*
4532  * ":doautocmd": Apply the automatic commands to the current buffer.
4533  */
4534  static void
4535 ex_doautocmd(exarg_T *eap)
4536 {
4537  char_u *arg = eap->arg;
4538  int call_do_modelines = check_nomodeline(&arg);
4539  int did_aucmd;
4540 
4541  (void)do_doautocmd(arg, TRUE, &did_aucmd);
4542  /* Only when there is no <nomodeline>. */
4543  if (call_do_modelines && did_aucmd)
4544  do_modelines(0);
4545 }
4546 
4547 /*
4548  * :[N]bunload[!] [N] [bufname] unload buffer
4549  * :[N]bdelete[!] [N] [bufname] delete buffer from buffer list
4550  * :[N]bwipeout[!] [N] [bufname] delete buffer really
4551  */
4552  static void
4553 ex_bunload(exarg_T *eap)
4554 {
4555  if (ERROR_IF_POPUP_WINDOW)
4556  return;
4557  eap->errmsg = do_bufdel(
4558  eap->cmdidx == CMD_bdelete ? DOBUF_DEL
4559  : eap->cmdidx == CMD_bwipeout ? DOBUF_WIPE
4560  : DOBUF_UNLOAD, eap->arg,
4561  eap->addr_count, (int)eap->line1, (int)eap->line2, eap->forceit);
4562 }

4567  */

4569 ex_buffer(exarg_T *eap)
4570 {

4572  return;

4579  else
4580  goto_buffer(eap, DOBUF_FIRST, FORWARD, (int)eap->line2);
4581  if (eap->do_ecmd_cmd != NULL)
4582  do_cmdline_cmd(eap->do_ecmd_cmd);
4583  }
4584 }

4650  int
4651 ends_excmd(int c)
4652 {
4653  return (c == NUL || c == '|' || c == '"' || c == '\n');
4654 }

4656 #if defined(FEAT_SYN_HL) || defined(FEAT_SEARCH_EXTRA) || defined(FEAT_EVAL) \
4657  || defined(PROTO)
4658 /*
4659  * Return the next command, after the first '|' or '\n'.
4660  * Return NULL if not found.
4661  */
4662  char_u *
4663 find_nextcmd(char_u *p)
4664 {
4665  while (*p != '|' && *p != '\n')
4666  {
4667  if (*p == NUL)
4668  return NULL;
4669  ++p;
4670  }
4671  return (p + 1);
4672 }
4673 #endif

4675 /*
4676  * Check if *p is a separator between Ex commands, skipping over white space.
4677  * Return NULL if it isn't, the following character if it is.
4678  */
4679  char_u *
4680 check_nextcmd(char_u *p)
4681 {
4682  char_u *s = skipwhite(p);
4683 
4684  if (*s == '|' || *s == '\n')
4685  return (s + 1);
4686  else
4687  return NULL;
4688 }

4690 /*
4691  * - if there are more files to edit
4692  * - and this is the last window
4693  * - and forceit not used
4694  * - and not repeated twice on a row
4695  * return FAIL and give error message if 'message' TRUE
4696  * return OK otherwise
4697  */
4698  static int
4699 check_more(
4700  int message, /* when FALSE check only, no messages */
4701  int forceit)
4702 {
4703  int n = ARGCOUNT - curwin->w_arg_idx - 1;
4704 
4705  if (!forceit && only_one_window()
4706  && ARGCOUNT > 1 && !arg_had_last && n >= 0 && quitmore == 0)
4707  {
4708  if (message)
4709  {
4710 #if defined(FEAT_GUI_DIALOG) || defined(FEAT_CON_DIALOG)
4711  if ((p_confirm || cmdmod.confirm) && curbuf->b_fname != NULL)
4712  {
4713  char_u buff[DIALOG_MSG_SIZE];
4714 
4715  vim_snprintf((char *)buff, DIALOG_MSG_SIZE,
4716  NGETTEXT("%d more file to edit. Quit anyway?",
4717  "%d more files to edit. Quit anyway?", n), n);
4718  if (vim_dialog_yesno(VIM_QUESTION, NULL, buff, 1) == VIM_YES)
4719  return OK;
4720  return FAIL;
4721  }
4722 #endif
4723  semsg(NGETTEXT("E173: %d more file to edit",
4724  "E173: %d more files to edit", n), n);
4725  quitmore = 2; /* next try to quit is allowed */
4726  }
4727  return FAIL;
4728  }
4729  return OK;
4730 }

4792 /*
4793  * Call this function if we thought we were going to exit, but we won't
4794  * (because of an error). May need to restore the terminal mode.
4795  */
4796  void
4797 not_exiting(void)
4798 {
4799  exiting = FALSE;
4800  settmode(TMODE_RAW);
4801 }
4802 
4803  static int
4804 before_quit_autocmds(win_T *wp, int quit_all, int forceit)
4805 {
4806  apply_autocmds(EVENT_QUITPRE, NULL, NULL, FALSE, wp->w_buffer);
4807 
4808  /* Bail out when autocommands closed the window.
4809  * Refuse to quit when the buffer in the last window is being closed (can
4810  * only happen in autocommands). */
4811  if (!win_valid(wp)
4812  || curbuf_locked()
4813  || (wp->w_buffer->b_nwindows == 1 && wp->w_buffer->b_locked > 0))
4814  return TRUE;
4815 
4816  if (quit_all || (check_more(FALSE, forceit) == OK && only_one_window()))
4817  {
4818  apply_autocmds(EVENT_EXITPRE, NULL, NULL, FALSE, curbuf);
4819  /* Refuse to quit when locked or when the buffer in the last window is
4820  * being closed (can only happen in autocommands). */
4821  if (curbuf_locked()
4822  || (curbuf->b_nwindows == 1 && curbuf->b_locked > 0))
4823  return TRUE;
4824  }
4825 
4826  return FALSE;
4827 }
4828 
4829 /*
4830  * ":quit": quit current window, quit Vim if the last window is closed.
4831  * ":{nr}quit": quit window {nr}
4832  */
4833  static void
4834 ex_quit(exarg_T *eap)
4835 {
4836  win_T *wp;
4837 
4838 #ifdef FEAT_CMDWIN
4839  if (cmdwin_type != 0)
4840  {
4841  cmdwin_result = Ctrl_C;
4842  return;
4843  }
4844 #endif
4845  /* Don't quit while editing the command line. */
4846  if (text_locked())
4847  {
4848  text_locked_msg();
4849  return;
4850  }
4851  if (eap->addr_count > 0)
4852  {
4853  int wnr = eap->line2;
4854 
4855  for (wp = firstwin; wp->w_next != NULL; wp = wp->w_next)
4856  if (--wnr <= 0)
4857  break;
4858  }
4859  else
4860  wp = curwin;
4861 
4862  /* Refuse to quit when locked. */
4863  if (curbuf_locked())
4864  return;
4865 
4866  /* Trigger QuitPre and maybe ExitPre */
4867  if (before_quit_autocmds(wp, FALSE, eap->forceit))
4868  return;
4869 
4870 #ifdef FEAT_NETBEANS_INTG
4871  netbeansForcedQuit = eap->forceit;
4872 #endif
4873 
4874  /*
4875  * If there are more files or windows we won't exit.
4876  */
4877  if (check_more(FALSE, eap->forceit) == OK && only_one_window())
4878  exiting = TRUE;
4879  if ((!buf_hide(wp->w_buffer)
4880  && check_changed(wp->w_buffer, (p_awa ? CCGD_AW : 0)
4881  | (eap->forceit ? CCGD_FORCEIT : 0)
4882  | CCGD_EXCMD))
4883  || check_more(TRUE, eap->forceit) == FAIL
4884  || (only_one_window() && check_changed_any(eap->forceit, TRUE)))
4885  {
4886  not_exiting();
4887  }
4888  else
4889  {
4890  /* quit last window
4891  * Note: only_one_window() returns true, even so a help window is
4892  * still open. In that case only quit, if no address has been
4893  * specified. Example:
4894  * :h|wincmd w|1q - don't quit
4895  * :h|wincmd w|q - quit
4896  */
4897  if (only_one_window() && (ONE_WINDOW || eap->addr_count == 0))
4898  getout(0);
4899  not_exiting();
4900 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
4901  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
4902 #endif
4903  /* close window; may free buffer */
4904  win_close(wp, !buf_hide(wp->w_buffer) || eap->forceit);
4905  }
4906 }
4907 
4908 /*
4909  * ":cquit".
4910  */
4911  static void
4912 ex_cquit(exarg_T *eap UNUSED)
4913 {
4914  getout(1); /* this does not always pass on the exit code to the Manx
4915  compiler. why? */
4916 }

4918 /*
4919  * ":qall": try to quit all windows
4920  */
4921  static void
4922 ex_quit_all(exarg_T *eap)
4923 {
4924 # ifdef FEAT_CMDWIN
4925  if (cmdwin_type != 0)
4926  {
4927  if (eap->forceit)
4928  cmdwin_result = K_XF1; /* ex_window() takes care of this */
4929  else
4930  cmdwin_result = K_XF2;
4931  return;
4932  }
4933 # endif
4934 
4935  /* Don't quit while editing the command line. */
4936  if (text_locked())
4937  {
4938  text_locked_msg();
4939  return;
4940  }
4941 
4942  if (before_quit_autocmds(curwin, TRUE, eap->forceit))
4943  return;
4944 
4945  exiting = TRUE;
4946  if (eap->forceit || !check_changed_any(FALSE, FALSE))
4947  getout(0);
4948  not_exiting();
4949 }

4951 /*
4952  * ":close": close current window, unless it is the last one
4953  */
4954  static void
4955 ex_close(exarg_T *eap)
4956 {
4957  win_T *win;
4958  int winnr = 0;
4959 #ifdef FEAT_CMDWIN
4960  if (cmdwin_type != 0)
4961  cmdwin_result = Ctrl_C;
4962  else
4963 #endif
4964  if (!text_locked() && !curbuf_locked())
4965  {
4966  if (eap->addr_count == 0)
4967  ex_win_close(eap->forceit, curwin, NULL);
4968  else
4969  {
4970  FOR_ALL_WINDOWS(win)
4971  {
4972  winnr++;
4973  if (winnr == eap->line2)
4974  break;
4975  }
4976  if (win == NULL)
4977  win = lastwin;
4978  ex_win_close(eap->forceit, win, NULL);
4979  }
4980  }
4981 }

5006 /*
5007  * Close window "win" and take care of handling closing the last window for a
5008  * modified buffer.
5009  */
5010  static void
5011 ex_win_close(
5012  int forceit,
5013  win_T *win,
5014  tabpage_T *tp) /* NULL or the tab page "win" is in */
5015 {
5016  int need_hide;
5017  buf_T *buf = win->w_buffer;
5018 
5019  need_hide = (bufIsChanged(buf) && buf->b_nwindows <= 1);
5020  if (need_hide && !buf_hide(buf) && !forceit)
5021  {
5022 #if defined(FEAT_GUI_DIALOG) || defined(FEAT_CON_DIALOG)
5023  if ((p_confirm || cmdmod.confirm) && p_write)
5024  {
5025  bufref_T bufref;
5026 
5027  set_bufref(&bufref, buf);
5028  dialog_changed(buf, FALSE);
5029  if (bufref_valid(&bufref) && bufIsChanged(buf))
5030  return;
5031  need_hide = FALSE;
5032  }
5033  else
5034 #endif
5035  {
5036  no_write_message();
5037  return;
5038  }
5039  }
5040 
5041 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
5042  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
5043 #endif
5044 
5045  /* free buffer when not hiding it or when it's a scratch buffer */
5046  if (tp == NULL)
5047  win_close(win, !need_hide && !buf_hide(buf));
5048  else
5049  win_close_othertab(win, !need_hide && !buf_hide(buf), tp);
5050 }
5051 
5052 /*
5053  * Handle the argument for a tabpage related ex command.
5054  * Returns a tabpage number.
5055  * When an error is encountered then eap->errmsg is set.
5056  */
5057  static int
5058 get_tabpage_arg(exarg_T *eap)
5059 {
5060  int tab_number;
5061  int unaccept_arg0 = (eap->cmdidx == CMD_tabmove) ? 0 : 1;
5062 
5063  if (eap->arg && *eap->arg != NUL)
5064  {
5065  char_u *p = eap->arg;
5066  char_u *p_save;
5067  int relative = 0; /* argument +N/-N means: go to N places to the
5068  * right/left relative to the current position. */
5069 
5070  if (*p == '-')
5071  {
5072  relative = -1;
5073  p++;
5074  }
5075  else if (*p == '+')
5076  {
5077  relative = 1;
5078  p++;
5079  }
5080 
5081  p_save = p;
5082  tab_number = getdigits(&p);
5083 
5084  if (relative == 0)
5085  {
5086  if (STRCMP(p, "$") == 0)
5087  tab_number = LAST_TAB_NR;
5088  else if (p == p_save || *p_save == '-' || *p != NUL
5089  || tab_number > LAST_TAB_NR)
5090  {
5091  /* No numbers as argument. */
5092  eap->errmsg = e_invarg;
5093  goto theend;
5094  }
5095  }
5096  else
5097  {
5098  if (*p_save == NUL)
5099  tab_number = 1;
5100  else if (p == p_save || *p_save == '-' || *p != NUL
5101  || tab_number == 0)
5102  {
5103  /* No numbers as argument. */
5104  eap->errmsg = e_invarg;
5105  goto theend;
5106  }
5107  tab_number = tab_number * relative + tabpage_index(curtab);
5108  if (!unaccept_arg0 && relative == -1)
5109  --tab_number;
5110  }
5111  if (tab_number < unaccept_arg0 || tab_number > LAST_TAB_NR)
5112  eap->errmsg = e_invarg;
5113  }
5114  else if (eap->addr_count > 0)
5115  {
5116  if (unaccept_arg0 && eap->line2 == 0)
5117  {
5118  eap->errmsg = e_invrange;
5119  tab_number = 0;
5120  }
5121  else
5122  {
5123  tab_number = eap->line2;
5124  if (!unaccept_arg0 && *skipwhite(*eap->cmdlinep) == '-')
5125  {
5126  --tab_number;
5127  if (tab_number < unaccept_arg0)
5128  eap->errmsg = e_invarg;
5129  }
5130  }
5131  }
5132  else
5133  {
5134  switch (eap->cmdidx)
5135  {
5136  case CMD_tabnext:
5137  tab_number = tabpage_index(curtab) + 1;
5138  if (tab_number > LAST_TAB_NR)
5139  tab_number = 1;
5140  break;
5141  case CMD_tabmove:
5142  tab_number = LAST_TAB_NR;
5143  break;
5144  default:
5145  tab_number = tabpage_index(curtab);
5146  }
5147  }
5148 
5149 theend:
5150  return tab_number;
5151 }
5152 
5153 /*
5154  * ":tabclose": close current tab page, unless it is the last one.
5155  * ":tabclose N": close tab page N.
5156  */
5157  static void
5158 ex_tabclose(exarg_T *eap)
5159 {
5160  tabpage_T *tp;
5161  int tab_number;
5162 
5163 # ifdef FEAT_CMDWIN
5164  if (cmdwin_type != 0)
5165  cmdwin_result = K_IGNORE;
5166  else
5167 # endif
5168  if (first_tabpage->tp_next == NULL)
5169  emsg(_("E784: Cannot close last tab page"));
5170  else
5171  {
5172  tab_number = get_tabpage_arg(eap);
5173  if (eap->errmsg == NULL)
5174  {
5175  tp = find_tabpage(tab_number);
5176  if (tp == NULL)
5177  {
5178  beep_flush();
5179  return;
5180  }
5181  if (tp != curtab)
5182  {
5183  tabpage_close_other(tp, eap->forceit);
5184  return;
5185  }
5186  else if (!text_locked() && !curbuf_locked())
5187  tabpage_close(eap->forceit);
5188  }
5189  }
5190 }
5191 
5192 /*
5193  * ":tabonly": close all tab pages except the current one
5194  */
5195  static void
5196 ex_tabonly(exarg_T *eap)
5197 {
5198  tabpage_T *tp;
5199  int done;
5200  int tab_number;
5201 
5202 # ifdef FEAT_CMDWIN
5203  if (cmdwin_type != 0)
5204  cmdwin_result = K_IGNORE;
5205  else
5206 # endif
5207  if (first_tabpage->tp_next == NULL)
5208  msg(_("Already only one tab page"));
5209  else
5210  {
5211  tab_number = get_tabpage_arg(eap);
5212  if (eap->errmsg == NULL)
5213  {
5214  goto_tabpage(tab_number);
5215  /* Repeat this up to a 1000 times, because autocommands may
5216  * mess up the lists. */
5217  for (done = 0; done < 1000; ++done)
5218  {
5219  FOR_ALL_TABPAGES(tp)
5220  if (tp->tp_topframe != topframe)
5221  {
5222  tabpage_close_other(tp, eap->forceit);
5223  /* if we failed to close it quit */
5224  if (valid_tabpage(tp))
5225  done = 1000;
5226  /* start over, "tp" is now invalid */
5227  break;
5228  }
5229  if (first_tabpage->tp_next == NULL)
5230  break;
5231  }
5232  }
5233  }
5234 }
5235 
5236 /*
5237  * Close the current tab page.
5238  */
5239  void
5240 tabpage_close(int forceit)
5241 {
5242  /* First close all the windows but the current one. If that worked then
5243  * close the last window in this tab, that will close it. */
5244  if (!ONE_WINDOW)
5245  close_others(TRUE, forceit);
5246  if (ONE_WINDOW)
5247  ex_win_close(forceit, curwin, NULL);
5248 # ifdef FEAT_GUI
5249  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
5250 # endif
5251 }
5252 
5253 /*
5254  * Close tab page "tp", which is not the current tab page.
5255  * Note that autocommands may make "tp" invalid.
5256  * Also takes care of the tab pages line disappearing when closing the
5257  * last-but-one tab page.
5258  */
5259  void
5260 tabpage_close_other(tabpage_T *tp, int forceit)
5261 {
5262  int done = 0;
5263  win_T *wp;
5264  int h = tabline_height();
5265 
5266  /* Limit to 1000 windows, autocommands may add a window while we close
5267  * one. OK, so I'm paranoid... */
5268  while (++done < 1000)
5269  {
5270  wp = tp->tp_firstwin;
5271  ex_win_close(forceit, wp, tp);
5272 
5273  /* Autocommands may delete the tab page under our fingers and we may
5274  * fail to close a window with a modified buffer. */
5275  if (!valid_tabpage(tp) || tp->tp_firstwin == wp)
5276  break;
5277  }
5278 
5279  apply_autocmds(EVENT_TABCLOSED, NULL, NULL, FALSE, curbuf);
5280 
5281  redraw_tabline = TRUE;
5282  if (h != tabline_height())
5283  shell_new_rows();
5284 }

5286 /*
5287  * ":only".
5288  */
5289  static void
5290 ex_only(exarg_T *eap)
5291 {
5292  win_T *wp;
5293  int wnr;
5294 # ifdef FEAT_GUI
5295  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
5296 # endif
5297  if (eap->addr_count > 0)
5298  {
5299  wnr = eap->line2;
5300  for (wp = firstwin; --wnr > 0; )
5301  {
5302  if (wp->w_next == NULL)
5303  break;
5304  else
5305  wp = wp->w_next;
5306  }
5307  win_goto(wp);
5308  }
5309  close_others(TRUE, eap->forceit);
5310 }

5312  static void
5313 ex_hide(exarg_T *eap UNUSED)
5314 {
5315  /* ":hide" or ":hide | cmd": hide current window */
5316  if (!eap->skip)
5317  {
5318 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
5319  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
5320 #endif
5321  if (eap->addr_count == 0)
5322  win_close(curwin, FALSE); /* don't free buffer */
5323  else
5324  {
5325  int winnr = 0;
5326  win_T *win;
5327 
5328  FOR_ALL_WINDOWS(win)
5329  {
5330  winnr++;
5331  if (winnr == eap->line2)
5332  break;
5333  }
5334  if (win == NULL)
5335  win = lastwin;
5336  win_close(win, FALSE);
5337  }
5338  }
5339 }

5341 /*
5342  * ":stop" and ":suspend": Suspend Vim.
5343  */
5344  static void
5345 ex_stop(exarg_T *eap)
5346 {
5347  /*
5348  * Disallow suspending for "rvim".
5349  */
5350  if (!check_restricted())
5351  {
5352  if (!eap->forceit)
5353  autowrite_all();
5354  windgoto((int)Rows - 1, 0);
5355  out_char('\n');
5356  out_flush();
5357  stoptermcap();
5358  out_flush(); /* needed for SUN to restore xterm buffer */
5359 #ifdef FEAT_TITLE
5360  mch_restore_title(SAVE_RESTORE_BOTH); /* restore window titles */
5361 #endif
5362  ui_suspend(); /* call machine specific function */
5363 #ifdef FEAT_TITLE
5364  maketitle();
5365  resettitle(); /* force updating the title */
5366 #endif
5367  starttermcap();
5368  scroll_start(); /* scroll screen before redrawing */
5369  redraw_later_clear();
5370  shell_resized(); /* may have resized window */
5371  }
5372 }

5374 /*
5375  * ":exit", ":xit" and ":wq": Write file and quite the current window.
5376  */
5377  static void
5378 ex_exit(exarg_T *eap)
5379 {
5380 #ifdef FEAT_CMDWIN
5381  if (cmdwin_type != 0)
5382  {
5383  cmdwin_result = Ctrl_C;
5384  return;
5385  }
5386 #endif
5387  /* Don't quit while editing the command line. */
5388  if (text_locked())
5389  {
5390  text_locked_msg();
5391  return;
5392  }
5393 
5394  if (before_quit_autocmds(curwin, FALSE, eap->forceit))
5395  return;
5396 
5397  /*
5398  * if more files or windows we won't exit
5399  */
5400  if (check_more(FALSE, eap->forceit) == OK && only_one_window())
5401  exiting = TRUE;
5402  if ( ((eap->cmdidx == CMD_wq
5403  || curbufIsChanged())
5404  && do_write(eap) == FAIL)
5405  || check_more(TRUE, eap->forceit) == FAIL
5406  || (only_one_window() && check_changed_any(eap->forceit, FALSE)))
5407  {
5408  not_exiting();
5409  }
5410  else
5411  {
5412  if (only_one_window()) /* quit last window, exit Vim */
5413  getout(0);
5414  not_exiting();
5415 # ifdef FEAT_GUI
5416  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
5417 # endif
5418  /* Quit current window, may free the buffer. */
5419  win_close(curwin, !buf_hide(curwin->w_buffer));
5420  }
5421 }
5422 
5423 /*
5424  * ":print", ":list", ":number".
5425  */
5426  static void
5427 ex_print(exarg_T *eap)
5428 {
5429  if (curbuf->b_ml.ml_flags & ML_EMPTY)
5430  emsg(_(e_emptybuf));
5431  else
5432  {
5433  for ( ;!got_int; ui_breakcheck())
5434  {
5435  print_line(eap->line1,
5436  (eap->cmdidx == CMD_number || eap->cmdidx == CMD_pound
5437  || (eap->flags & EXFLAG_NR)),
5438  eap->cmdidx == CMD_list || (eap->flags & EXFLAG_LIST));
5439  if (++eap->line1 > eap->line2)
5440  break;
5441  out_flush(); /* show one line at a time */
5442  }
5443  setpcmark();
5444  /* put cursor at last line */
5445  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line2;
5446  beginline(BL_SOL | BL_FIX);
5447  }
5448 
5449  ex_no_reprint = TRUE;
5450 }

5460 /*
5461  * ":shell".
5462  */
5463  static void
5464 ex_shell(exarg_T *eap UNUSED)
5465 {
5466  do_shell(NULL, 0);
5467 }
5468 
5469 #if defined(HAVE_DROP_FILE) || defined(PROTO)
5470 
5471 static int drop_busy = FALSE;
5472 static int drop_filec;
5473 static char_u **drop_filev = NULL;
5474 static int drop_split;
5475 static void (*drop_callback)(void *);
5476 static void *drop_cookie;
5477 
5478  static void
5479 handle_drop_internal(void)
5480 {
5481  exarg_T ea;
5482  int save_msg_scroll = msg_scroll;
5483 
5484  // Setting the argument list may cause screen updates and being called
5485  // recursively. Avoid that by setting drop_busy.
5486  drop_busy = TRUE;
5487 
5488  /* Check whether the current buffer is changed. If so, we will need
5489  * to split the current window or data could be lost.
5490  * We don't need to check if the 'hidden' option is set, as in this
5491  * case the buffer won't be lost.
5492  */
5493  if (!buf_hide(curbuf) && !drop_split)
5494  {
5495  ++emsg_off;
5496  drop_split = check_changed(curbuf, CCGD_AW);
5497  --emsg_off;
5498  }
5499  if (drop_split)
5500  {
5501  if (win_split(0, 0) == FAIL)
5502  return;
5503  RESET_BINDING(curwin);
5504 
5505  /* When splitting the window, create a new alist. Otherwise the
5506  * existing one is overwritten. */
5507  alist_unlink(curwin->w_alist);
5508  alist_new();
5509  }
5510 
5511  /*
5512  * Set up the new argument list.
5513  */
5514  alist_set(ALIST(curwin), drop_filec, drop_filev, FALSE, NULL, 0);
5515 
5516  /*
5517  * Move to the first file.
5518  */
5519  /* Fake up a minimal "next" command for do_argfile() */
5520  vim_memset(&ea, 0, sizeof(ea));
5521  ea.cmd = (char_u *)"next";
5522  do_argfile(&ea, 0);
5523 
5524  /* do_ecmd() may set need_start_insertmode, but since we never left Insert
5525  * mode that is not needed here. */
5526  need_start_insertmode = FALSE;
5527 
5528  /* Restore msg_scroll, otherwise a following command may cause scrolling
5529  * unexpectedly. The screen will be redrawn by the caller, thus
5530  * msg_scroll being set by displaying a message is irrelevant. */
5531  msg_scroll = save_msg_scroll;
5532 
5533  if (drop_callback != NULL)
5534  drop_callback(drop_cookie);
5535 
5536  drop_filev = NULL;
5537  drop_busy = FALSE;
5538 }
5539 
5540 /*
5541  * Handle a file drop. The code is here because a drop is *nearly* like an
5542  * :args command, but not quite (we have a list of exact filenames, so we
5543  * don't want to (a) parse a command line, or (b) expand wildcards). So the
5544  * code is very similar to :args and hence needs access to a lot of the static
5545  * functions in this file.
5546  *
5547  * The "filev" list must have been allocated using alloc(), as should each item
5548  * in the list. This function takes over responsibility for freeing the "filev"
5549  * list.
5550  */
5551  void
5552 handle_drop(
5553  int filec, // the number of files dropped
5554  char_u **filev, // the list of files dropped
5555  int split, // force splitting the window
5556  void (*callback)(void *), // to be called after setting the argument
5557  // list
5558  void *cookie) // argument for "callback" (allocated)
5559 {
5560  // Cannot handle recursive drops, finish the pending one.
5561  if (drop_busy)
5562  {
5563  FreeWild(filec, filev);
5564  vim_free(cookie);
5565  return;
5566  }
5567 
5568  // When calling handle_drop() more than once in a row we only use the last
5569  // one.
5570  if (drop_filev != NULL)
5571  {
5572  FreeWild(drop_filec, drop_filev);
5573  vim_free(drop_cookie);
5574  }
5575 
5576  drop_filec = filec;
5577  drop_filev = filev;
5578  drop_split = split;
5579  drop_callback = callback;
5580  drop_cookie = cookie;
5581 
5582  // Postpone this when:
5583  // - editing the command line
5584  // - not possible to change the current buffer
5585  // - updating the screen
5586  // As it may change buffers and window structures that are in use and cause
5587  // freed memory to be used.
5588  if (text_locked() || curbuf_locked() || updating_screen)
5589  return;
5590 
5591  handle_drop_internal();
5592 }
5593 
5594 /*
5595  * To be called when text is unlocked, curbuf is unlocked or updating_screen is
5596  * reset: Handle a postponed drop.
5597  */
5598  void
5599 handle_any_postponed_drop(void)
5600 {
5601  if (!drop_busy && drop_filev != NULL
5602  && !text_locked() && !curbuf_locked() && !updating_screen)
5603  handle_drop_internal();
5604 }
5605 #endif
5606

5626  | CCGD_MULTWIN
5627  | (eap->forceit ? CCGD_FORCEIT : 0)
5628  | CCGD_EXCMD)
5629 
5630  && (*eap->arg == NUL
5631  || setfname(curbuf, eap->arg, NULL, TRUE) == OK))
5632  ml_recover(TRUE);
5633  recoverymode = FALSE;
5634 }

5645 /*
5646  * :sview [+command] file split window with new file, read-only
5647  * :split [[+command] file] split window with current or new file
5648  * :vsplit [[+command] file] split window vertically with current or new file
5649  * :new [[+command] file] split window with no or new file
5650  * :vnew [[+command] file] split vertically window with no or new file
5651  * :sfind [+command] file split window with file in 'path'
5652  *
5653  * :tabedit open new Tab page with empty window
5654  * :tabedit [+command] file open new Tab page and edit "file"
5655  * :tabnew [[+command] file] just like :tabedit
5656  * :tabfind [+command] file open new Tab page and find "file"
5657  */
5658  void
5659 ex_splitview(exarg_T *eap)
5660 {
5661  win_T *old_curwin = curwin;
5662 #if defined(FEAT_SEARCHPATH) || defined(FEAT_BROWSE)
5663  char_u *fname = NULL;
5664 #endif
5665 #ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
5666  int browse_flag = cmdmod.browse;
5667 #endif
5668  int use_tab = eap->cmdidx == CMD_tabedit
5669  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_tabfind
5670  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_tabnew;
5671 
5672  if (ERROR_IF_POPUP_WINDOW)
5673  return;
5674 
5675 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
5676  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
5677 #endif
5678 
5679 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
5680  /* A ":split" in the quickfix window works like ":new". Don't want two
5681  * quickfix windows. But it's OK when doing ":tab split". */
5682  if (bt_quickfix(curbuf) && cmdmod.tab == 0)
5683  {
5684  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_split)
5685  eap->cmdidx = CMD_new;
5686  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_vsplit)
5687  eap->cmdidx = CMD_vnew;
5688  }
5689 #endif
5690 
5691 #ifdef FEAT_SEARCHPATH
5692  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_sfind || eap->cmdidx == CMD_tabfind)
5693  {
5694  fname = find_file_in_path(eap->arg, (int)STRLEN(eap->arg),
5695  FNAME_MESS, TRUE, curbuf->b_ffname);
5696  if (fname == NULL)
5697  goto theend;
5698  eap->arg = fname;
5699  }
5700 # ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
5701  else
5702 # endif
5703 #endif
5704 #ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
5705  if (cmdmod.browse
5706  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_vnew
5707  && eap->cmdidx != CMD_new)
5708  {
5709  if (
5710 # ifdef FEAT_GUI
5711  !gui.in_use &&
5712 # endif
5713  au_has_group((char_u *)"FileExplorer"))
5714  {
5715  /* No browsing supported but we do have the file explorer:
5716  * Edit the directory. */
5717  if (*eap->arg == NUL || !mch_isdir(eap->arg))
5718  eap->arg = (char_u *)".";
5719  }
5720  else
5721  {
5722  fname = do_browse(0, (char_u *)(use_tab
5723  ? _("Edit File in new tab page")
5724  : _("Edit File in new window")),
5725  eap->arg, NULL, NULL, NULL, curbuf);
5726  if (fname == NULL)
5727  goto theend;
5728  eap->arg = fname;
5729  }
5730  }
5731  cmdmod.browse = FALSE; /* Don't browse again in do_ecmd(). */
5732 #endif
5733 
5734  /*
5735  * Either open new tab page or split the window.
5736  */
5737  if (use_tab)
5738  {
5739  if (win_new_tabpage(cmdmod.tab != 0 ? cmdmod.tab
5740  : eap->addr_count == 0 ? 0
5741  : (int)eap->line2 + 1) != FAIL)
5742  {
5743  do_exedit(eap, old_curwin);
5744 
5745  /* set the alternate buffer for the window we came from */
5746  if (curwin != old_curwin
5747  && win_valid(old_curwin)
5748  && old_curwin->w_buffer != curbuf
5749  && !cmdmod.keepalt)
5750  old_curwin->w_alt_fnum = curbuf->b_fnum;
5751  }
5752  }
5753  else if (win_split(eap->addr_count > 0 ? (int)eap->line2 : 0,
5754  *eap->cmd == 'v' ? WSP_VERT : 0) != FAIL)
5755  {
5756  /* Reset 'scrollbind' when editing another file, but keep it when
5757  * doing ":split" without arguments. */
5758  if (*eap->arg != NUL
5759 # ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
5760  || cmdmod.browse
5761 # endif
5762  )
5763  RESET_BINDING(curwin);
5764  else
5765  do_check_scrollbind(FALSE);
5766  do_exedit(eap, old_curwin);
5767  }
5768 
5769 # ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
5770  cmdmod.browse = browse_flag;
5771 # endif
5772 
5773 # if defined(FEAT_SEARCHPATH) || defined(FEAT_BROWSE)
5774 theend:
5775  vim_free(fname);
5776 # endif
5777 }
5778 
5779 /*
5780  * Open a new tab page.
5781  */
5782  void
5783 tabpage_new(void)
5784 {
5785  exarg_T ea;
5786 
5787  vim_memset(&ea, 0, sizeof(ea));
5788  ea.cmdidx = CMD_tabnew;
5789  ea.cmd = (char_u *)"tabn";
5790  ea.arg = (char_u *)"";
5791  ex_splitview(&ea);
5792 }

5794 /*
5795  * :tabnext command
5796  */
5797  static void
5798 ex_tabnext(exarg_T *eap)
5799 {
5800  int tab_number;
5801 
5802  if (ERROR_IF_POPUP_WINDOW)
5803  return;
5804  switch (eap->cmdidx)
5805  {
5806  case CMD_tabfirst:
5807  case CMD_tabrewind:
5808  goto_tabpage(1);
5809  break;
5810  case CMD_tablast:
5811  goto_tabpage(9999);
5812  break;
5813  case CMD_tabprevious:
5814  case CMD_tabNext:
5815  if (eap->arg && *eap->arg != NUL)
5816  {
5817  char_u *p = eap->arg;
5818  char_u *p_save = p;
5819 
5820  tab_number = getdigits(&p);
5821  if (p == p_save || *p_save == '-' || *p != NUL
5822  || tab_number == 0)
5823  {
5824  /* No numbers as argument. */
5825  eap->errmsg = e_invarg;
5826  return;
5827  }
5828  }
5829  else
5830  {
5831  if (eap->addr_count == 0)
5832  tab_number = 1;
5833  else
5834  {
5835  tab_number = eap->line2;
5836  if (tab_number < 1)
5837  {
5838  eap->errmsg = e_invrange;
5839  return;
5840  }
5841  }
5842  }
5843  goto_tabpage(-tab_number);
5844  break;
5845  default: /* CMD_tabnext */
5846  tab_number = get_tabpage_arg(eap);
5847  if (eap->errmsg == NULL)
5848  goto_tabpage(tab_number);
5849  break;
5850  }
5851 }

5854  * :tabmove command
5855  */

5857 ex_tabmove(exarg_T *eap)
5858 {
5859  int tab_number;
5860

5862  if (eap->errmsg == NULL)
5863  tabpage_move(tab_number);
5864 }
5865 
5866 /*
5867  * :tabs command: List tabs and their contents.
5868  */
5869  static void
5870 ex_tabs(exarg_T *eap UNUSED)
5871 {
5872  tabpage_T *tp;
5873  win_T *wp;
5874  int tabcount = 1;
5875 
5876  msg_start();
5877  msg_scroll = TRUE;
5878  for (tp = first_tabpage; tp != NULL && !got_int; tp = tp->tp_next)
5879  {
5880  msg_putchar('\n');
5881  vim_snprintf((char *)IObuff, IOSIZE, _("Tab page %d"), tabcount++);
5882  msg_outtrans_attr(IObuff, HL_ATTR(HLF_T));
5883  out_flush(); /* output one line at a time */
5884  ui_breakcheck();
5885 
5886  if (tp == curtab)
5887  wp = firstwin;
5888  else
5889  wp = tp->tp_firstwin;
5890  for ( ; wp != NULL && !got_int; wp = wp->w_next)
5891  {
5892  msg_putchar('\n');
5893  msg_putchar(wp == curwin ? '>' : ' ');
5894  msg_putchar(' ');
5895  msg_putchar(bufIsChanged(wp->w_buffer) ? '+' : ' ');
5896  msg_putchar(' ');
5897  if (buf_spname(wp->w_buffer) != NULL)
5898  vim_strncpy(IObuff, buf_spname(wp->w_buffer), IOSIZE - 1);
5899  else
5900  home_replace(wp->w_buffer, wp->w_buffer->b_fname,
5901  IObuff, IOSIZE, TRUE);
5902  msg_outtrans(IObuff);
5903  out_flush(); /* output one line at a time */
5904  ui_breakcheck();
5905  }
5906  }
5907 }

5922 /*
5923  * ":resize".
5924  * set, increment or decrement current window height
5925  */
5926  static void
5927 ex_resize(exarg_T *eap)
5928 {
5929  int n;
5930  win_T *wp = curwin;
5931 
5932  if (eap->addr_count > 0)
5933  {
5934  n = eap->line2;
5935  for (wp = firstwin; wp->w_next != NULL && --n > 0; wp = wp->w_next)
5936  ;
5937  }
5938 
5939 # ifdef FEAT_GUI
5940  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
5941 # endif
5942  n = atol((char *)eap->arg);
5943  if (cmdmod.split & WSP_VERT)
5944  {
5945  if (*eap->arg == '-' || *eap->arg == '+')
5946  n += curwin->w_width;
5947  else if (n == 0 && eap->arg[0] == NUL) /* default is very wide */
5948  n = 9999;
5949  win_setwidth_win((int)n, wp);
5950  }
5951  else
5952  {
5953  if (*eap->arg == '-' || *eap->arg == '+')
5954  n += curwin->w_height;
5955  else if (n == 0 && eap->arg[0] == NUL) /* default is very high */
5956  n = 9999;
5957  win_setheight_win((int)n, wp);
5958  }
5959 }
5960 
5961 /*
5962  * ":find [+command] <file>" command.
5963  */
5964  static void
5965 ex_find(exarg_T *eap)
5966 {
5967 #ifdef FEAT_SEARCHPATH
5968  char_u *fname;
5969  int count;
5970 
5971  fname = find_file_in_path(eap->arg, (int)STRLEN(eap->arg), FNAME_MESS,
5972  TRUE, curbuf->b_ffname);
5973  if (eap->addr_count > 0)
5974  {
5975  /* Repeat finding the file "count" times. This matters when it
5976  * appears several times in the path. */
5977  count = eap->line2;
5978  while (fname != NULL && --count > 0)
5979  {
5980  vim_free(fname);
5981  fname = find_file_in_path(NULL, 0, FNAME_MESS,
5982  FALSE, curbuf->b_ffname);
5983  }
5984  }
5985 
5986  if (fname != NULL)
5987  {
5988  eap->arg = fname;
5989 #endif
5990  do_exedit(eap, NULL);
5991 #ifdef FEAT_SEARCHPATH
5992  vim_free(fname);
5993  }
5994 #endif
5995 }

5997 /*
5998  * ":open" simulation: for now just work like ":visual".
5999  */
6000  static void
6001 ex_open(exarg_T *eap)
6002 {
6003  regmatch_T regmatch;
6004  char_u *p;
6005 
6006  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line2;
6007  beginline(BL_SOL | BL_FIX);
6008  if (*eap->arg == '/')
6009  {
6010  /* ":open /pattern/": put cursor in column found with pattern */
6011  ++eap->arg;
6012  p = skip_regexp(eap->arg, '/', p_magic, NULL);
6013  *p = NUL;
6014  regmatch.regprog = vim_regcomp(eap->arg, p_magic ? RE_MAGIC : 0);
6015  if (regmatch.regprog != NULL)
6016  {
6017  regmatch.rm_ic = p_ic;
6018  p = ml_get_curline();
6019  if (vim_regexec(&regmatch, p, (colnr_T)0))
6020  curwin->w_cursor.col = (colnr_T)(regmatch.startp[0] - p);
6021  else
6022  emsg(_(e_nomatch));
6023  vim_regfree(regmatch.regprog);
6024  }
6025  /* Move to the NUL, ignore any other arguments. */
6026  eap->arg += STRLEN(eap->arg);
6027  }
6028  check_cursor();
6029 
6030  eap->cmdidx = CMD_visual;
6031  do_exedit(eap, NULL);
6032 }
