6034 /*
6035  * ":edit", ":badd", ":visual".
6036  */
6037  static void
6038 ex_edit(exarg_T *eap)
6039 {
6040  do_exedit(eap, NULL);
6041 }
6042 
6043 /*
6044  * ":edit <file>" command and alikes.
6045  */
6046  void
6047 do_exedit(
6048  exarg_T *eap,
6049  win_T *old_curwin) /* curwin before doing a split or NULL */
6050 {
6051  int n;
6052  int need_hide;
6053  int exmode_was = exmode_active;
6054 
6055  if (eap->cmdidx != CMD_pedit && ERROR_IF_POPUP_WINDOW)
6056  return;
6057  /*
6058  * ":vi" command ends Ex mode.
6059  */
6060  if (exmode_active && (eap->cmdidx == CMD_visual
6061  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_view))
6062  {
6063  exmode_active = FALSE;
6064  if (*eap->arg == NUL)
6065  {
6066  /* Special case: ":global/pat/visual\NLvi-commands" */
6067  if (global_busy)
6068  {
6069  int rd = RedrawingDisabled;
6070  int nwr = no_wait_return;
6071  int ms = msg_scroll;
6072 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
6073  int he = hold_gui_events;
6074 #endif
6075 
6076  if (eap->nextcmd != NULL)
6077  {
6078  stuffReadbuff(eap->nextcmd);
6079  eap->nextcmd = NULL;
6080  }
6081 
6082  if (exmode_was != EXMODE_VIM)
6083  settmode(TMODE_RAW);
6084  RedrawingDisabled = 0;
6085  no_wait_return = 0;
6086  need_wait_return = FALSE;
6087  msg_scroll = 0;
6088 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
6089  hold_gui_events = 0;
6090 #endif
6091  must_redraw = CLEAR;
6092 
6093  main_loop(FALSE, TRUE);
6094 
6095  RedrawingDisabled = rd;
6096  no_wait_return = nwr;
6097  msg_scroll = ms;
6098 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
6099  hold_gui_events = he;
6100 #endif
6101  }
6102  return;
6103  }
6104  }
6105 
6106  if ((eap->cmdidx == CMD_new
6107  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_tabnew
6108  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_tabedit
6109  || eap->cmdidx == CMD_vnew) && *eap->arg == NUL)
6110  {
6111  /* ":new" or ":tabnew" without argument: edit an new empty buffer */
6112  setpcmark();
6113  (void)do_ecmd(0, NULL, NULL, eap, ECMD_ONE,
6114  ECMD_HIDE + (eap->forceit ? ECMD_FORCEIT : 0),
6115  old_curwin == NULL ? curwin : NULL);
6116  }
6117  else if ((eap->cmdidx != CMD_split && eap->cmdidx != CMD_vsplit)
6118  || *eap->arg != NUL
6119 #ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
6120  || cmdmod.browse
6121 #endif
6122  )
6123  {
6124  /* Can't edit another file when "curbuf_lock" is set. Only ":edit"
6125  * can bring us here, others are stopped earlier. */
6126  if (*eap->arg != NUL && curbuf_locked())
6127  return;
6128 
6129  n = readonlymode;
6130  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_view || eap->cmdidx == CMD_sview)
6131  readonlymode = TRUE;
6132  else if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_enew)
6133  readonlymode = FALSE; /* 'readonly' doesn't make sense in an
6134  empty buffer */
6135  setpcmark();
6136  if (do_ecmd(0, (eap->cmdidx == CMD_enew ? NULL : eap->arg),
6137  NULL, eap,
6138  /* ":edit" goes to first line if Vi compatible */
6139  (*eap->arg == NUL && eap->do_ecmd_lnum == 0
6140  && vim_strchr(p_cpo, CPO_GOTO1) != NULL)
6141  ? ECMD_ONE : eap->do_ecmd_lnum,
6142  (buf_hide(curbuf) ? ECMD_HIDE : 0)
6143  + (eap->forceit ? ECMD_FORCEIT : 0)
6144  /* after a split we can use an existing buffer */
6145  + (old_curwin != NULL ? ECMD_OLDBUF : 0)
6146  + (eap->cmdidx == CMD_badd ? ECMD_ADDBUF : 0 )
6147  , old_curwin == NULL ? curwin : NULL) == FAIL)
6148  {
6149  /* Editing the file failed. If the window was split, close it. */
6150  if (old_curwin != NULL)
6151  {
6152  need_hide = (curbufIsChanged() && curbuf->b_nwindows <= 1);
6153  if (!need_hide || buf_hide(curbuf))
6154  {
6155 #if defined(FEAT_EVAL)
6156  cleanup_T cs;
6157 
6158  /* Reset the error/interrupt/exception state here so that
6159  * aborting() returns FALSE when closing a window. */
6160  enter_cleanup(&cs);
6161 #endif
6162 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
6163  need_mouse_correct = TRUE;
6164 #endif
6165  win_close(curwin, !need_hide && !buf_hide(curbuf));
6166 
6167 #if defined(FEAT_EVAL)
6168  /* Restore the error/interrupt/exception state if not
6169  * discarded by a new aborting error, interrupt, or
6170  * uncaught exception. */
6171  leave_cleanup(&cs);
6172 #endif
6173  }
6174  }
6175  }
6176  else if (readonlymode && curbuf->b_nwindows == 1)
6177  {
6178  /* When editing an already visited buffer, 'readonly' won't be set
6179  * but the previous value is kept. With ":view" and ":sview" we
6180  * want the file to be readonly, except when another window is
6181  * editing the same buffer. */
6182  curbuf->b_p_ro = TRUE;
6183  }
6184  readonlymode = n;
6185  }
6186  else
6187  {
6188  if (eap->do_ecmd_cmd != NULL)
6189  do_cmdline_cmd(eap->do_ecmd_cmd);
6190 #ifdef FEAT_TITLE
6191  n = curwin->w_arg_idx_invalid;
6192 #endif
6193  check_arg_idx(curwin);
6194 #ifdef FEAT_TITLE
6195  if (n != curwin->w_arg_idx_invalid)
6196  maketitle();
6197 #endif
6198  }
6199 
6200  /*
6201  * if ":split file" worked, set alternate file name in old window to new
6202  * file
6203  */
6204  if (old_curwin != NULL
6205  && *eap->arg != NUL
6206  && curwin != old_curwin
6207  && win_valid(old_curwin)
6208  && old_curwin->w_buffer != curbuf
6209  && !cmdmod.keepalt)
6210  old_curwin->w_alt_fnum = curbuf->b_fnum;
6211 
6212  ex_no_reprint = TRUE;
6213 }

6261 /*
6262  * ":syncbind" forces all 'scrollbind' windows to have the same relative
6263  * offset.
6264  * (1998-11-02 16:21:01 R. Edward Ralston <eralston@computer.org>)
6265  */
6266  static void
6267 ex_syncbind(exarg_T *eap UNUSED)
6268 {
6269  win_T *wp;
6270  win_T *save_curwin = curwin;
6271  buf_T *save_curbuf = curbuf;
6272  long topline;
6273  long y;
6274  linenr_T old_linenr = curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
6275 
6276  setpcmark();
6277 
6278  /*
6279  * determine max topline
6280  */
6281  if (curwin->w_p_scb)
6282  {
6283  topline = curwin->w_topline;
6284  FOR_ALL_WINDOWS(wp)
6285  {
6286  if (wp->w_p_scb && wp->w_buffer)
6287  {
6288  y = wp->w_buffer->b_ml.ml_line_count - get_scrolloff_value();
6289  if (topline > y)
6290  topline = y;
6291  }
6292  }
6293  if (topline < 1)
6294  topline = 1;
6295  }
6296  else
6297  {
6298  topline = 1;
6299  }
6300 
6301 
6302  /*
6303  * Set all scrollbind windows to the same topline.
6304  */
6305  FOR_ALL_WINDOWS(curwin)
6306  {
6307  if (curwin->w_p_scb)
6308  {
6309  curbuf = curwin->w_buffer;
6310  y = topline - curwin->w_topline;
6311  if (y > 0)
6312  scrollup(y, TRUE);
6313  else
6314  scrolldown(-y, TRUE);
6315  curwin->w_scbind_pos = topline;
6316  redraw_later(VALID);
6317  cursor_correct();
6318  curwin->w_redr_status = TRUE;
6319  }
6320  }
6321  curwin = save_curwin;
6322  curbuf = save_curbuf;
6323  if (curwin->w_p_scb)
6324  {
6325  did_syncbind = TRUE;
6326  checkpcmark();
6327  if (old_linenr != curwin->w_cursor.lnum)
6328  {
6329  char_u ctrl_o[2];
6330 
6331  ctrl_o[0] = Ctrl_O;
6332  ctrl_o[1] = 0;
6333  ins_typebuf(ctrl_o, REMAP_NONE, 0, TRUE, FALSE);
6334  }
6335  }
6336 }
6337 
6338 
6339  static void
6340 ex_read(exarg_T *eap)
6341 {
6342  int i;
6343  int empty = (curbuf->b_ml.ml_flags & ML_EMPTY);
6344  linenr_T lnum;
6345 
6346  if (eap->usefilter) /* :r!cmd */
6347  do_bang(1, eap, FALSE, FALSE, TRUE);
6348  else
6349  {
6350  if (u_save(eap->line2, (linenr_T)(eap->line2 + 1)) == FAIL)
6351  return;
6352 
6353 #ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
6354  if (cmdmod.browse)
6355  {
6356  char_u *browseFile;
6357 
6358  browseFile = do_browse(0, (char_u *)_("Append File"), eap->arg,
6359  NULL, NULL, NULL, curbuf);
6360  if (browseFile != NULL)
6361  {
6362  i = readfile(browseFile, NULL,
6363  eap->line2, (linenr_T)0, (linenr_T)MAXLNUM, eap, 0);
6364  vim_free(browseFile);
6365  }
6366  else
6367  i = OK;
6368  }
6369  else
6370 #endif
6371  if (*eap->arg == NUL)
6372  {
6373  if (check_fname() == FAIL) /* check for no file name */
6374  return;
6375  i = readfile(curbuf->b_ffname, curbuf->b_fname,
6376  eap->line2, (linenr_T)0, (linenr_T)MAXLNUM, eap, 0);
6377  }
6378  else
6379  {
6380  if (vim_strchr(p_cpo, CPO_ALTREAD) != NULL)
6381  (void)setaltfname(eap->arg, eap->arg, (linenr_T)1);
6382  i = readfile(eap->arg, NULL,
6383  eap->line2, (linenr_T)0, (linenr_T)MAXLNUM, eap, 0);
6384 
6385  }
6386  if (i != OK)
6387  {
6388 #if defined(FEAT_EVAL)
6389  if (!aborting())
6390 #endif
6391  semsg(_(e_notopen), eap->arg);
6392  }
6393  else
6394  {
6395  if (empty && exmode_active)
6396  {
6397  /* Delete the empty line that remains. Historically ex does
6398  * this but vi doesn't. */
6399  if (eap->line2 == 0)
6400  lnum = curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count;
6401  else
6402  lnum = 1;
6403  if (*ml_get(lnum) == NUL && u_savedel(lnum, 1L) == OK)
6404  {
6405  ml_delete(lnum, FALSE);
6406  if (curwin->w_cursor.lnum > 1
6407  && curwin->w_cursor.lnum >= lnum)
6408  --curwin->w_cursor.lnum;
6409  deleted_lines_mark(lnum, 1L);
6410  }
6411  }
6412  redraw_curbuf_later(VALID);
6413  }
6414  }
6415 }
6416 
6417 static char_u *prev_dir = NULL;
6418 
6419 #if defined(EXITFREE) || defined(PROTO)
6420  void
6421 free_cd_dir(void)
6422 {
6423  VIM_CLEAR(prev_dir);
6424  VIM_CLEAR(globaldir);
6425 }
6426 #endif
6427 
6428 /*
6429  * Deal with the side effects of changing the current directory.
6430  * When 'scope' is CDSCOPE_TABPAGE then this was after an ":tcd" command.
6431  * When 'scope' is CDSCOPE_WINDOW then this was after an ":lcd" command.
6432  */
6433  void
6434 post_chdir(cdscope_T scope)
6435 {
6436  if (scope != CDSCOPE_WINDOW)
6437  // Clear tab local directory for both :cd and :tcd
6438  VIM_CLEAR(curtab->tp_localdir);
6439  VIM_CLEAR(curwin->w_localdir);
6440  if (scope != CDSCOPE_GLOBAL)
6441  {
6442  /* If still in global directory, need to remember current
6443  * directory as global directory. */
6444  if (globaldir == NULL && prev_dir != NULL)
6445  globaldir = vim_strsave(prev_dir);
6446  /* Remember this local directory for the window. */
6447  if (mch_dirname(NameBuff, MAXPATHL) == OK)
6448  {
6449  if (scope == CDSCOPE_TABPAGE)
6450  curtab->tp_localdir = vim_strsave(NameBuff);
6451  else
6452  curwin->w_localdir = vim_strsave(NameBuff);
6453  }
6454  }
6455  else
6456  {
6457  /* We are now in the global directory, no need to remember its
6458  * name. */
6459  VIM_CLEAR(globaldir);
6460  }
6461 
6462  shorten_fnames(TRUE);
6463 }
6464 
6465 /*
6466  * Change directory function used by :cd/:tcd/:lcd Ex commands and the
6467  * chdir() function. If 'winlocaldir' is TRUE, then changes the window-local
6468  * directory. If 'tablocaldir' is TRUE, then changes the tab-local directory.
6469  * Otherwise changes the global directory.
6470  * Returns TRUE if the directory is successfully changed.
6471  */
6472  int
6473 changedir_func(
6474  char_u *new_dir,
6475  int forceit,
6476  cdscope_T scope)
6477 {
6478  char_u *tofree;
6479  int dir_differs;
6480  int retval = FALSE;
6481 
6482  if (allbuf_locked())
6483  return FALSE;
6484 
6485  if (vim_strchr(p_cpo, CPO_CHDIR) != NULL && curbufIsChanged() && !forceit)
6486  {
6487  emsg(_("E747: Cannot change directory, buffer is modified (add ! to override)"));
6488  return FALSE;
6489  }
6490 
6491  // ":cd -": Change to previous directory
6492  if (STRCMP(new_dir, "-") == 0)
6493  {
6494  if (prev_dir == NULL)
6495  {
6496  emsg(_("E186: No previous directory"));
6497  return FALSE;
6498  }
6499  new_dir = prev_dir;
6500  }
6501 
6502  // Save current directory for next ":cd -"
6503  tofree = prev_dir;
6504  if (mch_dirname(NameBuff, MAXPATHL) == OK)
6505  prev_dir = vim_strsave(NameBuff);
6506  else
6507  prev_dir = NULL;
6508 
6509 #if defined(UNIX) || defined(VMS)
6510  // for UNIX ":cd" means: go to home directory
6511  if (*new_dir == NUL)
6512  {
6513  // use NameBuff for home directory name
6514 # ifdef VMS
6515  char_u *p;
6516 
6517  p = mch_getenv((char_u *)"SYS$LOGIN");
6518  if (p == NULL || *p == NUL) // empty is the same as not set
6519  NameBuff[0] = NUL;
6520  else
6521  vim_strncpy(NameBuff, p, MAXPATHL - 1);
6522 # else
6523  expand_env((char_u *)"$HOME", NameBuff, MAXPATHL);
6524 # endif
6525  new_dir = NameBuff;
6526  }
6527 #endif
6528  dir_differs = new_dir == NULL || prev_dir == NULL
6529  || pathcmp((char *)prev_dir, (char *)new_dir, -1) != 0;
6530  if (new_dir == NULL || (dir_differs && vim_chdir(new_dir)))
6531  emsg(_(e_failed));
6532  else
6533  {
6534  char_u *acmd_fname;
6535 
6536  post_chdir(scope);
6537 
6538  if (dir_differs)
6539  {
6540  if (scope == CDSCOPE_WINDOW)
6541  acmd_fname = (char_u *)"window";
6542  else if (scope == CDSCOPE_TABPAGE)
6543  acmd_fname = (char_u *)"tabpage";
6544  else
6545  acmd_fname = (char_u *)"global";
6546  apply_autocmds(EVENT_DIRCHANGED, acmd_fname, new_dir, FALSE,
6547  curbuf);
6548  }
6549  retval = TRUE;
6550  }
6551  vim_free(tofree);
6552 
6553  return retval;
6554 }
6555 
6556 /*
6557  * ":cd", ":tcd", ":lcd", ":chdir" ":tchdir" and ":lchdir".
6558  */
6559  void
6560 ex_cd(exarg_T *eap)
6561 {
6562  char_u *new_dir;
6563 
6564  new_dir = eap->arg;
6565 #if !defined(UNIX) && !defined(VMS)
6566  // for non-UNIX ":cd" means: print current directory
6567  if (*new_dir == NUL)
6568  ex_pwd(NULL);
6569  else
6570 #endif
6571  {
6572  cdscope_T scope = CDSCOPE_GLOBAL;
6573 
6574  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_lcd || eap->cmdidx == CMD_lchdir)
6575  scope = CDSCOPE_WINDOW;
6576  else if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_tcd || eap->cmdidx == CMD_tchdir)
6577  scope = CDSCOPE_TABPAGE;
6578 
6579  if (changedir_func(new_dir, eap->forceit, scope))
6580  {
6581  // Echo the new current directory if the command was typed.
6582  if (KeyTyped || p_verbose >= 5)
6583  ex_pwd(eap);
6584  }
6585  }
6586 }
6587 
6588 /*
6589  * ":pwd".
6590  */
6591  static void
6592 ex_pwd(exarg_T *eap UNUSED)
6593 {
6594  if (mch_dirname(NameBuff, MAXPATHL) == OK)
6595  {
6596 #ifdef BACKSLASH_IN_FILENAME
6597  slash_adjust(NameBuff);
6598 #endif
6599  msg((char *)NameBuff);
6600  }
6601  else
6602  emsg(_("E187: Unknown"));
6603 }
6604 
6605 /*
6606  * ":=".
6607  */
6608  static void
6609 ex_equal(exarg_T *eap)
6610 {
6611  smsg("%ld", (long)eap->line2);
6612  ex_may_print(eap);
6613 }
6614 
6615  static void
6616 ex_sleep(exarg_T *eap)
6617 {
6618  int n;
6619  long len;
6620 
6621  if (cursor_valid())
6622  {
6623  n = W_WINROW(curwin) + curwin->w_wrow - msg_scrolled;
6624  if (n >= 0)
6625  windgoto((int)n, curwin->w_wincol + curwin->w_wcol);
6626  }
6627 
6628  len = eap->line2;
6629  switch (*eap->arg)
6630  {
6631  case 'm': break;
6632  case NUL: len *= 1000L; break;
6633  default: semsg(_(e_invarg2), eap->arg); return;
6634  }
6635  do_sleep(len);
6636 }
6637 
6638 /*
6639  * Sleep for "msec" milliseconds, but keep checking for a CTRL-C every second.
6640  */
6641  void
6642 do_sleep(long msec)
6643 {
6644  long done = 0;
6645  long wait_now;
6646 # ifdef ELAPSED_FUNC
6647  elapsed_T start_tv;
6648 
6649  // Remember at what time we started, so that we know how much longer we
6650  // should wait after waiting for a bit.
6651  ELAPSED_INIT(start_tv);
6652 # endif
6653 
6654  cursor_on();
6655  out_flush_cursor(FALSE, FALSE);
6656  while (!got_int && done < msec)
6657  {
6658  wait_now = msec - done > 1000L ? 1000L : msec - done;
6659 #ifdef FEAT_TIMERS
6660  {
6661  long due_time = check_due_timer();
6662 
6663  if (due_time > 0 && due_time < wait_now)
6664  wait_now = due_time;
6665  }
6666 #endif
6667 #ifdef FEAT_JOB_CHANNEL
6668  if (has_any_channel() && wait_now > 20L)
6669  wait_now = 20L;
6670 #endif
6671 #ifdef FEAT_SOUND
6672  if (has_any_sound_callback() && wait_now > 20L)
6673  wait_now = 20L;
6674 #endif
6675  ui_delay(wait_now, TRUE);
6676 
6677 #ifdef FEAT_JOB_CHANNEL
6678  if (has_any_channel())
6679  ui_breakcheck_force(TRUE);
6680  else
6681 #endif
6682  ui_breakcheck();
6683 #ifdef MESSAGE_QUEUE
6684  // Process the netbeans and clientserver messages that may have been
6685  // received in the call to ui_breakcheck() when the GUI is in use. This
6686  // may occur when running a test case.
6687  parse_queued_messages();
6688 #endif
6689 
6690 # ifdef ELAPSED_FUNC
6691  // actual time passed
6692  done = ELAPSED_FUNC(start_tv);
6693 # else
6694  // guestimate time passed (will actually be more)
6695  done += wait_now;
6696 # endif
6697  }
6698 
6699  // If CTRL-C was typed to interrupt the sleep, drop the CTRL-C from the
6700  // input buffer, otherwise a following call to input() fails.
6701  if (got_int)
6702  (void)vpeekc();
6703 }

6706  * ":winsize" command (obsolete).
6707  */

6709 ex_winsize(exarg_T *eap)
6710 {

6712  char_u *arg = eap->arg;

6716  arg = skipwhite(arg);
6717  p = arg;
6718  h = getdigits(&arg);
6719  if (*p != NUL && *arg == NUL)
6720  set_shellsize(w, h, TRUE);
6721  else
6722  emsg(_("E465: :winsize requires two number arguments"));
6723 }

6725  static void
6726 ex_wincmd(exarg_T *eap)
6727 {
6728  int xchar = NUL;
6729  char_u *p;
6730 
6731  if (*eap->arg == 'g' || *eap->arg == Ctrl_G)
6732  {
6733  /* CTRL-W g and CTRL-W CTRL-G have an extra command character */
6734  if (eap->arg[1] == NUL)
6735  {
6736  emsg(_(e_invarg));
6737  return;
6738  }
6739  xchar = eap->arg[1];
6740  p = eap->arg + 2;
6741  }
6742  else
6743  p = eap->arg + 1;
6744 
6745  eap->nextcmd = check_nextcmd(p);
6746  p = skipwhite(p);
6747  if (*p != NUL && *p != '"' && eap->nextcmd == NULL)
6748  emsg(_(e_invarg));
6749  else if (!eap->skip)
6750  {
6751  /* Pass flags on for ":vertical wincmd ]". */
6752  postponed_split_flags = cmdmod.split;
6753  postponed_split_tab = cmdmod.tab;
6754  do_window(*eap->arg, eap->addr_count > 0 ? eap->line2 : 0L, xchar);
6755  postponed_split_flags = 0;
6756  postponed_split_tab = 0;
6757  }
6758 }

6810 # if defined(HAVE_TGETENT) || defined(VIMDLL)
6811  else

6813 # endif

6816 # endif

6819  term_set_winpos(x, y);

6821  }

6825 /*
6826  * Handle command that work like operators: ":delete", ":yank", ":>" and ":<".
6827  */
6828  static void
6829 ex_operators(exarg_T *eap)
6830 {
6831  oparg_T oa;
6832 
6833  clear_oparg(&oa);
6834  oa.regname = eap->regname;
6835  oa.start.lnum = eap->line1;
6836  oa.end.lnum = eap->line2;
6837  oa.line_count = eap->line2 - eap->line1 + 1;
6838  oa.motion_type = MLINE;
6839  virtual_op = FALSE;
6840  if (eap->cmdidx != CMD_yank) /* position cursor for undo */
6841  {
6842  setpcmark();
6843  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line1;
6844  beginline(BL_SOL | BL_FIX);
6845  }
6846 
6847  if (VIsual_active)
6848  end_visual_mode();
6849 
6850  switch (eap->cmdidx)
6851  {
6852  case CMD_delete:
6853  oa.op_type = OP_DELETE;
6854  op_delete(&oa);
6855  break;
6856 
6857  case CMD_yank:
6858  oa.op_type = OP_YANK;
6859  (void)op_yank(&oa, FALSE, TRUE);
6860  break;
6861 
6862  default: /* CMD_rshift or CMD_lshift */
6863  if (
6864 #ifdef FEAT_RIGHTLEFT
6865  (eap->cmdidx == CMD_rshift) ^ curwin->w_p_rl
6866 #else
6867  eap->cmdidx == CMD_rshift
6868 #endif
6869  )
6870  oa.op_type = OP_RSHIFT;
6871  else
6872  oa.op_type = OP_LSHIFT;
6873  op_shift(&oa, FALSE, eap->amount);
6874  break;
6875  }
6876  virtual_op = MAYBE;
6877  ex_may_print(eap);
6878 }

6881  * ":put".
6882  */
6883  static void
6884 ex_put(exarg_T *eap)
6885 {

6888  {
6889  eap->line2 = 1;
6890  eap->forceit = TRUE;
6891  }
6892  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line2;
6893  do_put(eap->regname, eap->forceit ? BACKWARD : FORWARD, 1L,
6894  PUT_LINE|PUT_CURSLINE);
6895 }

6897 /*
6898  * Handle ":copy" and ":move".
6899  */
6900  static void
6901 ex_copymove(exarg_T *eap)
6902 {
6903  long n;
6904 
6905  n = get_address(eap, &eap->arg, eap->addr_type, FALSE, FALSE, FALSE, 1);
6906  if (eap->arg == NULL) /* error detected */
6907  {
6908  eap->nextcmd = NULL;
6909  return;
6910  }
6911  get_flags(eap);
6912 
6913  /*
6914  * move or copy lines from 'eap->line1'-'eap->line2' to below line 'n'
6915  */
6916  if (n == MAXLNUM || n < 0 || n > curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count)
6917  {
6918  emsg(_(e_invrange));
6919  return;
6920  }
6921 
6922  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_move)
6923  {
6924  if (do_move(eap->line1, eap->line2, n) == FAIL)
6925  return;
6926  }
6927  else
6928  ex_copy(eap->line1, eap->line2, n);
6929  u_clearline();
6930  beginline(BL_SOL | BL_FIX);
6931  ex_may_print(eap);
6932 }

6963  */

6966 {
6967  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line1;
6968  if (eap->line1 == eap->line2)
6969  {
6970  if (eap->addr_count >= 2) /* :2,2join does nothing */
6971  return;
6972  if (eap->line2 == curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count)
6973  {
6974  beep_flush();
6975  return;
6976  }
6977  ++eap->line2;

6984 /*
6985  * ":[addr]@r" or ":[addr]*r": execute register
6986  */
6987  static void
6988 ex_at(exarg_T *eap)
6989 {
6990  int c;
6991  int prev_len = typebuf.tb_len;
6992 
6993  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line2;
6994  check_cursor_col();
6995 
6996 #ifdef USE_ON_FLY_SCROLL
6997  dont_scroll = TRUE; /* disallow scrolling here */
6998 #endif
6999 
7000  /* get the register name. No name means to use the previous one */
7001  c = *eap->arg;
7002  if (c == NUL || (c == '*' && *eap->cmd == '*'))
7003  c = '@';
7004  /* Put the register in the typeahead buffer with the "silent" flag. */
7005  if (do_execreg(c, TRUE, vim_strchr(p_cpo, CPO_EXECBUF) != NULL, TRUE)
7006  == FAIL)
7007  {
7008  beep_flush();
7009  }
7010  else
7011  {
7012  int save_efr = exec_from_reg;
7013 
7014  exec_from_reg = TRUE;
7015 
7016  /*
7017  * Execute from the typeahead buffer.
7018  * Continue until the stuff buffer is empty and all added characters
7019  * have been consumed.
7020  */
7021  while (!stuff_empty() || typebuf.tb_len > prev_len)
7022  (void)do_cmdline(NULL, getexline, NULL, DOCMD_NOWAIT|DOCMD_VERBOSE);
7023 
7024  exec_from_reg = save_efr;
7025  }
7026 }

7078 /*
7079  * ":earlier" and ":later".
7080  */
7081  static void
7082 ex_later(exarg_T *eap)
7083 {
7084  long count = 0;
7085  int sec = FALSE;
7086  int file = FALSE;
7087  char_u *p = eap->arg;
7088 
7089  if (*p == NUL)
7090  count = 1;
7091  else if (isdigit(*p))
7092  {
7093  count = getdigits(&p);
7094  switch (*p)
7095  {
7096  case 's': ++p; sec = TRUE; break;
7097  case 'm': ++p; sec = TRUE; count *= 60; break;
7098  case 'h': ++p; sec = TRUE; count *= 60 * 60; break;
7099  case 'd': ++p; sec = TRUE; count *= 24 * 60 * 60; break;
7100  case 'f': ++p; file = TRUE; break;
7101  }
7102  }
7103 
7104  if (*p != NUL)
7105  semsg(_(e_invarg2), eap->arg);
7106  else
7107  undo_time(eap->cmdidx == CMD_earlier ? -count : count,
7108  sec, file, FALSE);
7109 }

7111 /*
7112  * ":redir": start/stop redirection.
7113  */
7114  static void
7115 ex_redir(exarg_T *eap)
7116 {
7117  char *mode;
7118  char_u *fname;
7119  char_u *arg = eap->arg;
7120 
7121 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
7122  if (redir_execute)
7123  {
7124  emsg(_("E930: Cannot use :redir inside execute()"));
7125  return;
7126  }
7127 #endif
7128 
7129  if (STRICMP(eap->arg, "END") == 0)
7130  close_redir();
7131  else
7132  {
7133  if (*arg == '>')
7134  {
7135  ++arg;
7136  if (*arg == '>')
7137  {
7138  ++arg;
7139  mode = "a";
7140  }
7141  else
7142  mode = "w";
7143  arg = skipwhite(arg);
7144 
7145  close_redir();
7146 
7147  /* Expand environment variables and "~/". */
7148  fname = expand_env_save(arg);
7149  if (fname == NULL)
7150  return;
7151 #ifdef FEAT_BROWSE
7152  if (cmdmod.browse)
7153  {
7154  char_u *browseFile;
7155 
7156  browseFile = do_browse(BROWSE_SAVE,
7157  (char_u *)_("Save Redirection"),
7158  fname, NULL, NULL,
7159  (char_u *)_(BROWSE_FILTER_ALL_FILES), curbuf);
7160  if (browseFile == NULL)
7161  return; /* operation cancelled */
7162  vim_free(fname);
7163  fname = browseFile;
7164  eap->forceit = TRUE; /* since dialog already asked */
7165  }
7166 #endif
7167 
7168  redir_fd = open_exfile(fname, eap->forceit, mode);
7169  vim_free(fname);
7170  }
7171 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
7172  else if (*arg == '@')
7173  {
7174  /* redirect to a register a-z (resp. A-Z for appending) */
7175  close_redir();
7176  ++arg;
7177  if (ASCII_ISALPHA(*arg)
7178 # ifdef FEAT_CLIPBOARD
7179  || *arg == '*'
7180  || *arg == '+'
7181 # endif
7182  || *arg == '"')
7183  {
7184  redir_reg = *arg++;
7185  if (*arg == '>' && arg[1] == '>') /* append */
7186  arg += 2;
7187  else
7188  {
7189  /* Can use both "@a" and "@a>". */
7190  if (*arg == '>')
7191  arg++;
7192  /* Make register empty when not using @A-@Z and the
7193  * command is valid. */
7194  if (*arg == NUL && !isupper(redir_reg))
7195  write_reg_contents(redir_reg, (char_u *)"", -1, FALSE);
7196  }
7197  }
7198  if (*arg != NUL)
7199  {
7200  redir_reg = 0;
7201  semsg(_(e_invarg2), eap->arg);
7202  }
7203  }
7204  else if (*arg == '=' && arg[1] == '>')
7205  {
7206  int append;
7207 
7208  /* redirect to a variable */
7209  close_redir();
7210  arg += 2;
7211 
7212  if (*arg == '>')
7213  {
7214  ++arg;
7215  append = TRUE;
7216  }
7217  else
7218  append = FALSE;
7219 
7220  if (var_redir_start(skipwhite(arg), append) == OK)
7221  redir_vname = 1;
7222  }
7223 #endif
7224 
7225  /* TODO: redirect to a buffer */
7226 
7227  else
7228  semsg(_(e_invarg2), eap->arg);
7229  }
7230 
7231  /* Make sure redirection is not off. Can happen for cmdline completion
7232  * that indirectly invokes a command to catch its output. */
7233  if (redir_fd != NULL
7234 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
7235  || redir_reg || redir_vname
7236 #endif
7237  )
7238  redir_off = FALSE;
7239 }

7241 /*
7242  * ":redraw": force redraw
7243  */
7244  void
7245 ex_redraw(exarg_T *eap)
7246 {
7247  int r = RedrawingDisabled;
7248  int p = p_lz;
7249 
7250  RedrawingDisabled = 0;
7251  p_lz = FALSE;
7252  validate_cursor();
7253  update_topline();
7254  update_screen(eap->forceit ? CLEAR : VIsual_active ? INVERTED : 0);
7255 #ifdef FEAT_TITLE
7256  if (need_maketitle)
7257  maketitle();
7258 #endif
7259 #if defined(MSWIN) && (!defined(FEAT_GUI_MSWIN) || defined(VIMDLL))
7260 # ifdef VIMDLL
7261  if (!gui.in_use)
7262 # endif
7263  resize_console_buf();
7264 #endif
7265  RedrawingDisabled = r;
7266  p_lz = p;
7267 
7268  /* Reset msg_didout, so that a message that's there is overwritten. */
7269  msg_didout = FALSE;
7270  msg_col = 0;
7271 
7272  /* No need to wait after an intentional redraw. */
7273  need_wait_return = FALSE;
7274 
7275  out_flush();
7276 }

7318  static void
7319 close_redir(void)
7320 {
7321  if (redir_fd != NULL)
7322  {
7323  fclose(redir_fd);
7324  redir_fd = NULL;
7325  }
7326 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
7327  redir_reg = 0;
7328  if (redir_vname)
7329  {
7330  var_redir_stop();
7331  redir_vname = 0;
7332  }
7333 #endif
7334 }

7336 #if (defined(FEAT_SESSION) || defined(FEAT_EVAL)) || defined(PROTO)

7338 vim_mkdir_emsg(char_u *name, int prot UNUSED)
7339 {
7340  if (vim_mkdir(name, prot) != 0)
7341  {
7342  semsg(_("E739: Cannot create directory: %s"), name);
7343  return FAIL;
7344  }

7349 /*
7350  * Open a file for writing for an Ex command, with some checks.
7351  * Return file descriptor, or NULL on failure.
7352  */
7353  FILE *
7354 open_exfile(
7355  char_u *fname,
7356  int forceit,
7357  char *mode) /* "w" for create new file or "a" for append */
7358 {
7359  FILE *fd;
7360 
7361 #ifdef UNIX
7362  /* with Unix it is possible to open a directory */
7363  if (mch_isdir(fname))
7364  {
7365  semsg(_(e_isadir2), fname);
7366  return NULL;
7367  }
7368 #endif
7369  if (!forceit && *mode != 'a' && vim_fexists(fname))
7370  {
7371  semsg(_("E189: \"%s\" exists (add ! to override)"), fname);
7372  return NULL;
7373  }
7374 
7375  if ((fd = mch_fopen((char *)fname, mode)) == NULL)
7376  semsg(_("E190: Cannot open \"%s\" for writing"), fname);
7377 
7378  return fd;
7379 }

7381 /*
7382  * ":mark" and ":k".
7383  */
7384  static void
7385 ex_mark(exarg_T *eap)
7386 {
7387  pos_T pos;
7388 
7389  if (*eap->arg == NUL) /* No argument? */
7390  emsg(_(e_argreq));
7391  else if (eap->arg[1] != NUL) /* more than one character? */
7392  emsg(_(e_trailing));
7393  else
7394  {
7395  pos = curwin->w_cursor; /* save curwin->w_cursor */
7396  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line2;
7397  beginline(BL_WHITE | BL_FIX);
7398  if (setmark(*eap->arg) == FAIL) /* set mark */
7399  emsg(_("E191: Argument must be a letter or forward/backward quote"));
7400  curwin->w_cursor = pos; /* restore curwin->w_cursor */
7401  }
7402 }

7404 /*
7405  * Update w_topline, w_leftcol and the cursor position.
7406  */
7407  void
7408 update_topline_cursor(void)
7409 {
7410  check_cursor(); /* put cursor on valid line */
7411  update_topline();
7412  if (!curwin->w_p_wrap)
7413  validate_cursor();
7414  update_curswant();
7415 }
7416 
7417 /*
7418  * Save the current State and go to Normal mode.
7419  * Return TRUE if the typeahead could be saved.
7420  */
7421  int
7422 save_current_state(save_state_T *sst)
7423 {
7424  sst->save_msg_scroll = msg_scroll;
7425  sst->save_restart_edit = restart_edit;
7426  sst->save_msg_didout = msg_didout;
7427  sst->save_State = State;
7428  sst->save_insertmode = p_im;
7429  sst->save_finish_op = finish_op;
7430  sst->save_opcount = opcount;
7431  sst->save_reg_executing = reg_executing;
7432 
7433  msg_scroll = FALSE; /* no msg scrolling in Normal mode */
7434  restart_edit = 0; /* don't go to Insert mode */
7435  p_im = FALSE; /* don't use 'insertmode' */
7436 
7437  /*
7438  * Save the current typeahead. This is required to allow using ":normal"
7439  * from an event handler and makes sure we don't hang when the argument
7440  * ends with half a command.
7441  */
7442  save_typeahead(&sst->tabuf);
7443  return sst->tabuf.typebuf_valid;
7444 }
7445 
7446  void
7447 restore_current_state(save_state_T *sst)
7448 {
7449  /* Restore the previous typeahead. */
7450  restore_typeahead(&sst->tabuf);
7451 
7452  msg_scroll = sst->save_msg_scroll;
7453  restart_edit = sst->save_restart_edit;
7454  p_im = sst->save_insertmode;
7455  finish_op = sst->save_finish_op;
7456  opcount = sst->save_opcount;
7457  reg_executing = sst->save_reg_executing;
7458  msg_didout |= sst->save_msg_didout; /* don't reset msg_didout now */
7459 
7460  /* Restore the state (needed when called from a function executed for
7461  * 'indentexpr'). Update the mouse and cursor, they may have changed. */
7462  State = sst->save_State;
7463 #ifdef CURSOR_SHAPE
7464  ui_cursor_shape(); /* may show different cursor shape */
7465 #endif
7466 }
7467 
7468 /*
7469  * ":normal[!] {commands}": Execute normal mode commands.
7470  */
7471  void
7472 ex_normal(exarg_T *eap)
7473 {
7474  save_state_T save_state;
7475  char_u *arg = NULL;
7476  int l;
7477  char_u *p;
7478 
7479  if (ex_normal_lock > 0)
7480  {
7481  emsg(_(e_secure));
7482  return;
7483  }
7484  if (ex_normal_busy >= p_mmd)
7485  {
7486  emsg(_("E192: Recursive use of :normal too deep"));
7487  return;
7488  }
7489 
7490  /*
7491  * vgetc() expects a CSI and K_SPECIAL to have been escaped. Don't do
7492  * this for the K_SPECIAL leading byte, otherwise special keys will not
7493  * work.
7494  */
7495  if (has_mbyte)
7496  {
7497  int len = 0;
7498 
7499  /* Count the number of characters to be escaped. */
7500  for (p = eap->arg; *p != NUL; ++p)
7501  {
7502 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
7503  if (*p == CSI) /* leadbyte CSI */
7504  len += 2;
7505 #endif
7506  for (l = (*mb_ptr2len)(p) - 1; l > 0; --l)
7507  if (*++p == K_SPECIAL /* trailbyte K_SPECIAL or CSI */
7508 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
7509  || *p == CSI
7510 #endif
7511  )
7512  len += 2;
7513  }
7514  if (len > 0)
7515  {
7516  arg = alloc(STRLEN(eap->arg) + len + 1);
7517  if (arg != NULL)
7518  {
7519  len = 0;
7520  for (p = eap->arg; *p != NUL; ++p)
7521  {
7522  arg[len++] = *p;
7523 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
7524  if (*p == CSI)
7525  {
7526  arg[len++] = KS_EXTRA;
7527  arg[len++] = (int)KE_CSI;
7528  }
7529 #endif
7530  for (l = (*mb_ptr2len)(p) - 1; l > 0; --l)
7531  {
7532  arg[len++] = *++p;
7533  if (*p == K_SPECIAL)
7534  {
7535  arg[len++] = KS_SPECIAL;
7536  arg[len++] = KE_FILLER;
7537  }
7538 #ifdef FEAT_GUI
7539  else if (*p == CSI)
7540  {
7541  arg[len++] = KS_EXTRA;
7542  arg[len++] = (int)KE_CSI;
7543  }
7544 #endif
7545  }
7546  arg[len] = NUL;
7547  }
7548  }
7549  }
7550  }
7551 
7552  ++ex_normal_busy;
7553  if (save_current_state(&save_state))
7554  {
7555  /*
7556  * Repeat the :normal command for each line in the range. When no
7557  * range given, execute it just once, without positioning the cursor
7558  * first.
7559  */
7560  do
7561  {
7562  if (eap->addr_count != 0)
7563  {
7564  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = eap->line1++;
7565  curwin->w_cursor.col = 0;
7566  check_cursor_moved(curwin);
7567  }
7568 
7569  exec_normal_cmd(arg != NULL
7570  ? arg
7571  : eap->arg, eap->forceit ? REMAP_NONE : REMAP_YES, FALSE);
7572  }
7573  while (eap->addr_count > 0 && eap->line1 <= eap->line2 && !got_int);
7574  }
7575 
7576  /* Might not return to the main loop when in an event handler. */
7577  update_topline_cursor();
7578 
7579  restore_current_state(&save_state);
7580  --ex_normal_busy;
7581  setmouse();
7582 #ifdef CURSOR_SHAPE
7583  ui_cursor_shape(); /* may show different cursor shape */
7584 #endif
7585 
7586  vim_free(arg);
7587 }
7588 
7589 /*
7590  * ":startinsert", ":startreplace" and ":startgreplace"
7591  */
7592  static void
7593 ex_startinsert(exarg_T *eap)
7594 {
7595  if (eap->forceit)
7596  {
7597  // cursor line can be zero on startup
7598  if (!curwin->w_cursor.lnum)
7599  curwin->w_cursor.lnum = 1;
7600  set_cursor_for_append_to_line();
7601  }
7602 
7603  // Ignore the command when already in Insert mode. Inserting an
7604  // expression register that invokes a function can do this.
7605  if (State & INSERT)
7606  return;
7607 
7608  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_startinsert)
7609  restart_edit = 'a';
7610  else if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_startreplace)
7611  restart_edit = 'R';
7612  else
7613  restart_edit = 'V';
7614 
7615  if (!eap->forceit)
7616  {
7617  if (eap->cmdidx == CMD_startinsert)
7618  restart_edit = 'i';
7619  curwin->w_curswant = 0; // avoid MAXCOL
7620  }
7621 }
7622 
7623 /*
7624  * ":stopinsert"
7625  */
7626  static void
7627 ex_stopinsert(exarg_T *eap UNUSED)
7628 {
7629  restart_edit = 0;
7630  stop_insert_mode = TRUE;
7631  clearmode();
7632 }
7633 
7634 /*
7635  * Execute normal mode command "cmd".
7636  * "remap" can be REMAP_NONE or REMAP_YES.
7637  */
7638  void
7639 exec_normal_cmd(char_u *cmd, int remap, int silent)
7640 {
7641  /* Stuff the argument into the typeahead buffer. */
7642  ins_typebuf(cmd, remap, 0, TRUE, silent);
7643  exec_normal(FALSE, FALSE, FALSE);
7644 }
7645 
7646 /*
7647  * Execute normal_cmd() until there is no typeahead left.
7648  * When "use_vpeekc" is TRUE use vpeekc() to check for available chars.
7649  */
7650  void
7651 exec_normal(int was_typed, int use_vpeekc, int may_use_terminal_loop UNUSED)
7652 {
7653  oparg_T oa;
7654  int c;
7655 
7656  // When calling vpeekc() from feedkeys() it will return Ctrl_C when there
7657  // is nothing to get, so also check for Ctrl_C.
7658  clear_oparg(&oa);
7659  finish_op = FALSE;
7660  while ((!stuff_empty()
7661  || ((was_typed || !typebuf_typed()) && typebuf.tb_len > 0)
7662  || (use_vpeekc && (c = vpeekc()) != NUL && c != Ctrl_C))
7663  && !got_int)
7664  {
7665  update_topline_cursor();
7666 #ifdef FEAT_TERMINAL
7667  if (may_use_terminal_loop && term_use_loop()
7668  && oa.op_type == OP_NOP && oa.regname == NUL
7669  && !VIsual_active)
7670  {
7671  /* If terminal_loop() returns OK we got a key that is handled
7672  * in Normal model. With FAIL we first need to position the
7673  * cursor and the screen needs to be redrawn. */
7674  if (terminal_loop(TRUE) == OK)
7675  normal_cmd(&oa, TRUE);
7676  }
7677  else
7678 #endif
7679  /* execute a Normal mode cmd */
7680  normal_cmd(&oa, TRUE);
7681  }
7682 }
7683 
7684 #ifdef FEAT_FIND_ID
7685  static void
7686 ex_checkpath(exarg_T *eap)
7687 {
7688  find_pattern_in_path(NULL, 0, 0, FALSE, FALSE, CHECK_PATH, 1L,
7689  eap->forceit ? ACTION_SHOW_ALL : ACTION_SHOW,
7690  (linenr_T)1, (linenr_T)MAXLNUM);
7691 }
7692 
7693 #if defined(FEAT_QUICKFIX)
7694 /*
7695  * ":psearch"
7696  */
7697  static void
7698 ex_psearch(exarg_T *eap)
7699 {
7700  g_do_tagpreview = p_pvh;
7701  ex_findpat(eap);
7702  g_do_tagpreview = 0;
7703 }
7704 #endif
7705 
7706  static void
7707 ex_findpat(exarg_T *eap)
7708 {
7709  int whole = TRUE;
7710  long n;
7711  char_u *p;
7712  int action;
7713 
7714  switch (cmdnames[eap->cmdidx].cmd_name[2])
7715  {
7716  case 'e': /* ":psearch", ":isearch" and ":dsearch" */
7717  if (cmdnames[eap->cmdidx].cmd_name[0] == 'p')
7718  action = ACTION_GOTO;
7719  else
7720  action = ACTION_SHOW;
7721  break;
7722  case 'i': /* ":ilist" and ":dlist" */
7723  action = ACTION_SHOW_ALL;
7724  break;
7725  case 'u': /* ":ijump" and ":djump" */
7726  action = ACTION_GOTO;
7727  break;
7728  default: /* ":isplit" and ":dsplit" */
7729  action = ACTION_SPLIT;
7730  break;
7731  }
7732 
7733  n = 1;
7734  if (vim_isdigit(*eap->arg)) /* get count */
7735  {
7736  n = getdigits(&eap->arg);
7737  eap->arg = skipwhite(eap->arg);
7738  }
7739  if (*eap->arg == '/') /* Match regexp, not just whole words */
7740  {
7741  whole = FALSE;
7742  ++eap->arg;
7743  p = skip_regexp(eap->arg, '/', p_magic, NULL);
7744  if (*p)
7745  {
7746  *p++ = NUL;
7747  p = skipwhite(p);
7748 
7749  /* Check for trailing illegal characters */
7750  if (!ends_excmd(*p))
7751  eap->errmsg = e_trailing;
7752  else
7753  eap->nextcmd = check_nextcmd(p);
7754  }
7755  }
7756  if (!eap->skip)
7757  find_pattern_in_path(eap->arg, 0, (int)STRLEN(eap->arg),
7758  whole, !eap->forceit,
7759  *eap->cmd == 'd' ? FIND_DEFINE : FIND_ANY,
7760  n, action, eap->line1, eap->line2);
7761 }
7762 #endif
7763 
7764 
7765 #ifdef FEAT_QUICKFIX
7766 /*
7767  * ":ptag", ":ptselect", ":ptjump", ":ptnext", etc.
7768  */
7769  static void
7770 ex_ptag(exarg_T *eap)
7771 {
7772  g_do_tagpreview = p_pvh; /* will be reset to 0 in ex_tag_cmd() */
7773  ex_tag_cmd(eap, cmdnames[eap->cmdidx].cmd_name + 1);
7774 }

7776 /*
7777  * ":pedit"
7778  */
7779  static void
7780 ex_pedit(exarg_T *eap)
7781 {
7782  win_T *curwin_save = curwin;
7783 
7784  // Open the preview window or popup and make it the current window.
7785  g_do_tagpreview = p_pvh;
7786  prepare_tagpreview(TRUE, TRUE, FALSE);
7787 
7788  // Edit the file.
7789  do_exedit(eap, NULL);
7790 
7791  if (curwin != curwin_save && win_valid(curwin_save))
7792  {
7793  // Return cursor to where we were
7794  validate_cursor();
7795  redraw_later(VALID);
7796  win_enter(curwin_save, TRUE);
7797  }
7798 # ifdef FEAT_TEXT_PROP
7799  else if (WIN_IS_POPUP(curwin))
7800  {
7801  // can't keep focus in popup window
7802  win_enter(firstwin, TRUE);
7803  }
7804 # endif
7805  g_do_tagpreview = 0;
7806 }
7807 #endif

7809 /*
7810  * ":stag", ":stselect" and ":stjump".
7811  */
7812  static void
7813 ex_stag(exarg_T *eap)

7818  ex_tag_cmd(eap, cmdnames[eap->cmdidx].cmd_name + 1);
7819  postponed_split_flags = 0;

7822 
7823 /*
7824  * ":tag", ":tselect", ":tjump", ":tnext", etc.
7825  */
7826  static void
7827 ex_tag(exarg_T *eap)
7828 {
7829  ex_tag_cmd(eap, cmdnames[eap->cmdidx].cmd_name);
7830 }
7831 
7832  static void
7833 ex_tag_cmd(exarg_T *eap, char_u *name)
7834 {
7835  int cmd;
7836 
7837  switch (name[1])
7838  {
7839  case 'j': cmd = DT_JUMP; /* ":tjump" */
7840  break;
7841  case 's': cmd = DT_SELECT; /* ":tselect" */
7842  break;
7843  case 'p': cmd = DT_PREV; /* ":tprevious" */
7844  break;
7845  case 'N': cmd = DT_PREV; /* ":tNext" */
7846  break;
7847  case 'n': cmd = DT_NEXT; /* ":tnext" */
7848  break;
7849  case 'o': cmd = DT_POP; /* ":pop" */
7850  break;
7851  case 'f': /* ":tfirst" */
7852  case 'r': cmd = DT_FIRST; /* ":trewind" */
7853  break;
7854  case 'l': cmd = DT_LAST; /* ":tlast" */
7855  break;
7856  default: /* ":tag" */
7857 #ifdef FEAT_CSCOPE
7858  if (p_cst && *eap->arg != NUL)
7859  {
7860  ex_cstag(eap);
7861  return;
7862  }
7863 #endif
7864  cmd = DT_TAG;
7865  break;
7866  }
7867 
7868  if (name[0] == 'l')
7869  {
7870 #ifndef FEAT_QUICKFIX
7871  ex_ni(eap);
7872  return;
7873 #else
7874  cmd = DT_LTAG;
7875 #endif
7876  }
7877 
7878  do_tag(eap->arg, cmd, eap->addr_count > 0 ? (int)eap->line2 : 1,
7879  eap->forceit, TRUE);
7880 }
7881 
7882 /*
7883  * Check "str" for starting with a special cmdline variable.
7884  * If found return one of the SPEC_ values and set "*usedlen" to the length of
7885  * the variable. Otherwise return -1 and "*usedlen" is unchanged.
7886  */
7887  int
7888 find_cmdline_var(char_u *src, int *usedlen)
7889 {
7890  int len;
7891  int i;
7892  static char *(spec_str[]) = {
7893  "%",
7894 #define SPEC_PERC 0
7895  "#",
7896 #define SPEC_HASH (SPEC_PERC + 1)
7897  "<cword>", /* cursor word */
7898 #define SPEC_CWORD (SPEC_HASH + 1)
7899  "<cWORD>", /* cursor WORD */
7900 #define SPEC_CCWORD (SPEC_CWORD + 1)
7901  "<cexpr>", /* expr under cursor */
7902 #define SPEC_CEXPR (SPEC_CCWORD + 1)
7903  "<cfile>", /* cursor path name */
7904 #define SPEC_CFILE (SPEC_CEXPR + 1)
7905  "<sfile>", /* ":so" file name */
7906 #define SPEC_SFILE (SPEC_CFILE + 1)
7907  "<slnum>", /* ":so" file line number */
7908 #define SPEC_SLNUM (SPEC_SFILE + 1)
7909  "<afile>", /* autocommand file name */
7910 #define SPEC_AFILE (SPEC_SLNUM + 1)
7911  "<abuf>", /* autocommand buffer number */
7912 #define SPEC_ABUF (SPEC_AFILE + 1)
7913  "<amatch>", /* autocommand match name */
7914 #define SPEC_AMATCH (SPEC_ABUF + 1)
7915  "<sflnum>", /* script file line number */
7916 #define SPEC_SFLNUM (SPEC_AMATCH + 1)
7917 #ifdef FEAT_CLIENTSERVER
7918  "<client>"
7919 # define SPEC_CLIENT (SPEC_SFLNUM + 1)
7920 #endif
7921  };
7922 
7923  for (i = 0; i < (int)(sizeof(spec_str) / sizeof(char *)); ++i)
7924  {
7925  len = (int)STRLEN(spec_str[i]);
7926  if (STRNCMP(src, spec_str[i], len) == 0)
7927  {
7928  *usedlen = len;
7929  return i;
7930  }
7931  }
7932  return -1;
7933 }
7934 
7935 /*
7936  * Evaluate cmdline variables.
7937  *
7938  * change '%' to curbuf->b_ffname
7939  * '#' to curwin->w_altfile
7940  * '<cword>' to word under the cursor
7941  * '<cWORD>' to WORD under the cursor
7942  * '<cexpr>' to C-expression under the cursor
7943  * '<cfile>' to path name under the cursor
7944  * '<sfile>' to sourced file name
7945  * '<slnum>' to sourced file line number
7946  * '<afile>' to file name for autocommand
7947  * '<abuf>' to buffer number for autocommand
7948  * '<amatch>' to matching name for autocommand
7949  *
7950  * When an error is detected, "errormsg" is set to a non-NULL pointer (may be
7951  * "" for error without a message) and NULL is returned.
7952  * Returns an allocated string if a valid match was found.
7953  * Returns NULL if no match was found. "usedlen" then still contains the
7954  * number of characters to skip.
7955  */
7956  char_u *
7957 eval_vars(
7958  char_u *src, /* pointer into commandline */
7959  char_u *srcstart, /* beginning of valid memory for src */
7960  int *usedlen, /* characters after src that are used */
7961  linenr_T *lnump, /* line number for :e command, or NULL */
7962  char **errormsg, /* pointer to error message */
7963  int *escaped) /* return value has escaped white space (can
7964  * be NULL) */
7965 {
7966  int i;
7967  char_u *s;
7968  char_u *result;
7969  char_u *resultbuf = NULL;
7970  int resultlen;
7971  buf_T *buf;
7972  int valid = VALID_HEAD + VALID_PATH; /* assume valid result */
7973  int spec_idx;
7974  int tilde_file = FALSE;
7975  int skip_mod = FALSE;
7976  char_u strbuf[30];
7977 
7978  *errormsg = NULL;
7979  if (escaped != NULL)
7980  *escaped = FALSE;
7981 
7982  /*
7983  * Check if there is something to do.
7984  */
7985  spec_idx = find_cmdline_var(src, usedlen);
7986  if (spec_idx < 0) /* no match */
7987  {
7988  *usedlen = 1;
7989  return NULL;
7990  }
7991 
7992  /*
7993  * Skip when preceded with a backslash "\%" and "\#".
7994  * Note: In "\\%" the % is also not recognized!
7995  */
7996  if (src > srcstart && src[-1] == '\\')
7997  {
7998  *usedlen = 0;
7999  STRMOVE(src - 1, src); /* remove backslash */
8000  return NULL;
8001  }
8002 
8003  /*
8004  * word or WORD under cursor
8005  */
8006  if (spec_idx == SPEC_CWORD || spec_idx == SPEC_CCWORD
8007  || spec_idx == SPEC_CEXPR)
8008  {
8009  resultlen = find_ident_under_cursor(&result,
8010  spec_idx == SPEC_CWORD ? (FIND_IDENT | FIND_STRING)
8011  : spec_idx == SPEC_CEXPR ? (FIND_IDENT | FIND_STRING | FIND_EVAL)
8012  : FIND_STRING);
8013  if (resultlen == 0)
8014  {
8015  *errormsg = "";
8016  return NULL;
8017  }
8018  }
8019 
8020  /*
8021  * '#': Alternate file name
8022  * '%': Current file name
8023  * File name under the cursor
8024  * File name for autocommand
8025  * and following modifiers
8026  */
8027  else
8028  {
8029  switch (spec_idx)
8030  {
8031  case SPEC_PERC: /* '%': current file */
8032  if (curbuf->b_fname == NULL)
8033  {
8034  result = (char_u *)"";
8035  valid = 0; /* Must have ":p:h" to be valid */
8036  }
8037  else
8038  {
8039  result = curbuf->b_fname;
8040  tilde_file = STRCMP(result, "~") == 0;
8041  }
8042  break;
8043 
8044  case SPEC_HASH: /* '#' or "#99": alternate file */
8045  if (src[1] == '#') /* "##": the argument list */
8046  {
8047  result = arg_all();
8048  resultbuf = result;
8049  *usedlen = 2;
8050  if (escaped != NULL)
8051  *escaped = TRUE;
8052  skip_mod = TRUE;
8053  break;
8054  }
8055  s = src + 1;
8056  if (*s == '<') /* "#<99" uses v:oldfiles */
8057  ++s;
8058  i = (int)getdigits(&s);
8059  if (s == src + 2 && src[1] == '-')
8060  /* just a minus sign, don't skip over it */
8061  s--;
8062  *usedlen = (int)(s - src); /* length of what we expand */
8063 
8064  if (src[1] == '<' && i != 0)
8065  {
8066  if (*usedlen < 2)
8067  {
8068  /* Should we give an error message for #<text? */
8069  *usedlen = 1;
8070  return NULL;
8071  }
8072 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
8073  result = list_find_str(get_vim_var_list(VV_OLDFILES),
8074  (long)i);
8075  if (result == NULL)
8076  {
8077  *errormsg = "";
8078  return NULL;
8079  }
8080 #else
8081  *errormsg = _("E809: #< is not available without the +eval feature");
8082  return NULL;
8083 #endif
8084  }
8085  else
8086  {
8087  if (i == 0 && src[1] == '<' && *usedlen > 1)
8088  *usedlen = 1;
8089  buf = buflist_findnr(i);
8090  if (buf == NULL)
8091  {
8092  *errormsg = _("E194: No alternate file name to substitute for '#'");
8093  return NULL;
8094  }
8095  if (lnump != NULL)
8096  *lnump = ECMD_LAST;
8097  if (buf->b_fname == NULL)
8098  {
8099  result = (char_u *)"";
8100  valid = 0; /* Must have ":p:h" to be valid */
8101  }
8102  else
8103  {
8104  result = buf->b_fname;
8105  tilde_file = STRCMP(result, "~") == 0;
8106  }
8107  }
8108  break;
8109 
8110 #ifdef FEAT_SEARCHPATH
8111  case SPEC_CFILE: /* file name under cursor */
8112  result = file_name_at_cursor(FNAME_MESS|FNAME_HYP, 1L, NULL);
8113  if (result == NULL)
8114  {
8115  *errormsg = "";
8116  return NULL;
8117  }
8118  resultbuf = result; /* remember allocated string */
8119  break;
8120 #endif
8121 
8122  case SPEC_AFILE: /* file name for autocommand */
8123  result = autocmd_fname;
8124  if (result != NULL && !autocmd_fname_full)
8125  {
8126  /* Still need to turn the fname into a full path. It is
8127  * postponed to avoid a delay when <afile> is not used. */
8128  autocmd_fname_full = TRUE;
8129  result = FullName_save(autocmd_fname, FALSE);
8130  vim_free(autocmd_fname);
8131  autocmd_fname = result;
8132  }
8133  if (result == NULL)
8134  {
8135  *errormsg = _("E495: no autocommand file name to substitute for \"<afile>\"");
8136  return NULL;
8137  }
8138  result = shorten_fname1(result);
8139  break;
8140 
8141  case SPEC_ABUF: /* buffer number for autocommand */
8142  if (autocmd_bufnr <= 0)
8143  {
8144  *errormsg = _("E496: no autocommand buffer number to substitute for \"<abuf>\"");
8145  return NULL;
8146  }
8147  sprintf((char *)strbuf, "%d", autocmd_bufnr);
8148  result = strbuf;
8149  break;
8150 
8151  case SPEC_AMATCH: /* match name for autocommand */
8152  result = autocmd_match;
8153  if (result == NULL)
8154  {
8155  *errormsg = _("E497: no autocommand match name to substitute for \"<amatch>\"");
8156  return NULL;
8157  }
8158  break;
8159 
8160  case SPEC_SFILE: /* file name for ":so" command */
8161  result = sourcing_name;
8162  if (result == NULL)
8163  {
8164  *errormsg = _("E498: no :source file name to substitute for \"<sfile>\"");
8165  return NULL;
8166  }
8167  break;
8168 
8169  case SPEC_SLNUM: /* line in file for ":so" command */
8170  if (sourcing_name == NULL || sourcing_lnum == 0)
8171  {
8172  *errormsg = _("E842: no line number to use for \"<slnum>\"");
8173  return NULL;
8174  }
8175  sprintf((char *)strbuf, "%ld", (long)sourcing_lnum);
8176  result = strbuf;
8177  break;
8178 
8179 #ifdef FEAT_EVAL
8180  case SPEC_SFLNUM: /* line in script file */
8181  if (current_sctx.sc_lnum + sourcing_lnum == 0)
8182  {
8183  *errormsg = _("E961: no line number to use for \"<sflnum>\"");
8184  return NULL;
8185  }
8186  sprintf((char *)strbuf, "%ld",
8187  (long)(current_sctx.sc_lnum + sourcing_lnum));
8188  result = strbuf;
8189  break;
8190 #endif
8191 
8192 #ifdef FEAT_CLIENTSERVER
8193  case SPEC_CLIENT: /* Source of last submitted input */
8194  sprintf((char *)strbuf, PRINTF_HEX_LONG_U,
8195  (long_u)clientWindow);
8196  result = strbuf;
8197  break;
8198 #endif
8199 
8200  default:
8201  result = (char_u *)""; /* avoid gcc warning */
8202  break;
8203  }
8204 
8205  resultlen = (int)STRLEN(result); /* length of new string */
8206  if (src[*usedlen] == '<') /* remove the file name extension */
8207  {
8208  ++*usedlen;
8209  if ((s = vim_strrchr(result, '.')) != NULL && s >= gettail(result))
8210  resultlen = (int)(s - result);
8211  }
8212  else if (!skip_mod)
8213  {
8214  valid |= modify_fname(src, tilde_file, usedlen, &result, &resultbuf,
8215  &resultlen);
8216  if (result == NULL)
8217  {
8218  *errormsg = "";
8219  return NULL;
8220  }
8221  }
8222  }
8223 
8224  if (resultlen == 0 || valid != VALID_HEAD + VALID_PATH)
8225  {
8226  if (valid != VALID_HEAD + VALID_PATH)
8227  /* xgettext:no-c-format */
8228  *errormsg = _("E499: Empty file name for '%' or '#', only works with \":p:h\"");
8229  else
8230  *errormsg = _("E500: Evaluates to an empty string");
8231  result = NULL;
8232  }
8233  else
8234  result = vim_strnsave(result, resultlen);
8235  vim_free(resultbuf);
8236  return result;
8237 }
8238 
8239 /*
8240  * Expand the <sfile> string in "arg".
8241  *
8242  * Returns an allocated string, or NULL for any error.
8243  */
8244  char_u *
8245 expand_sfile(char_u *arg)
8246 {
8247  char *errormsg;
8248  int len;
8249  char_u *result;
8250  char_u *newres;
8251  char_u *repl;
8252  int srclen;
8253  char_u *p;
8254 
8255  result = vim_strsave(arg);
8256  if (result == NULL)
8257  return NULL;
8258 
8259  for (p = result; *p; )
8260  {
8261  if (STRNCMP(p, "<sfile>", 7) != 0)
8262  ++p;
8263  else
8264  {
8265  /* replace "<sfile>" with the sourced file name, and do ":" stuff */
8266  repl = eval_vars(p, result, &srclen, NULL, &errormsg, NULL);
8267  if (errormsg != NULL)
8268  {
8269  if (*errormsg)
8270  emsg(errormsg);
8271  vim_free(result);
8272  return NULL;
8273  }
8274  if (repl == NULL) /* no match (cannot happen) */
8275  {
8276  p += srclen;
8277  continue;
8278  }
8279  len = (int)STRLEN(result) - srclen + (int)STRLEN(repl) + 1;
8280  newres = alloc(len);
8281  if (newres == NULL)
8282  {
8283  vim_free(repl);
8284  vim_free(result);
8285  return NULL;
8286  }
8287  mch_memmove(newres, result, (size_t)(p - result));
8288  STRCPY(newres + (p - result), repl);
8289  len = (int)STRLEN(newres);
8290  STRCAT(newres, p + srclen);
8291  vim_free(repl);
8292  vim_free(result);
8293  result = newres;
8294  p = newres + len; /* continue after the match */
8295  }
8296  }
8297 
8298  return result;
8299 }

8340 static int filetype_detect = FALSE;
8341 static int filetype_plugin = FALSE;
8342 static int filetype_indent = FALSE;
8343 
8344 /*
8345  * ":filetype [plugin] [indent] {on,off,detect}"
8346  * on: Load the filetype.vim file to install autocommands for file types.
8347  * off: Load the ftoff.vim file to remove all autocommands for file types.
8348  * plugin on: load filetype.vim and ftplugin.vim
8349  * plugin off: load ftplugof.vim
8350  * indent on: load filetype.vim and indent.vim
8351  * indent off: load indoff.vim
8352  */
8353  static void
8354 ex_filetype(exarg_T *eap)
8355 {
8356  char_u *arg = eap->arg;
8357  int plugin = FALSE;
8358  int indent = FALSE;
8359 
8360  if (*eap->arg == NUL)
8361  {
8362  /* Print current status. */
8363  smsg("filetype detection:%s plugin:%s indent:%s",
8364  filetype_detect ? "ON" : "OFF",
8365  filetype_plugin ? (filetype_detect ? "ON" : "(on)") : "OFF",
8366  filetype_indent ? (filetype_detect ? "ON" : "(on)") : "OFF");
8367  return;
8368  }
8369 
8370  /* Accept "plugin" and "indent" in any order. */
8371  for (;;)
8372  {
8373  if (STRNCMP(arg, "plugin", 6) == 0)
8374  {
8375  plugin = TRUE;
8376  arg = skipwhite(arg + 6);
8377  continue;
8378  }
8379  if (STRNCMP(arg, "indent", 6) == 0)
8380  {
8381  indent = TRUE;
8382  arg = skipwhite(arg + 6);
8383  continue;
8384  }
8385  break;
8386  }
8387  if (STRCMP(arg, "on") == 0 || STRCMP(arg, "detect") == 0)
8388  {
8389  if (*arg == 'o' || !filetype_detect)
8390  {
8391  source_runtime((char_u *)FILETYPE_FILE, DIP_ALL);
8392  filetype_detect = TRUE;
8393  if (plugin)
8394  {
8395  source_runtime((char_u *)FTPLUGIN_FILE, DIP_ALL);
8396  filetype_plugin = TRUE;
8397  }
8398  if (indent)
8399  {
8400  source_runtime((char_u *)INDENT_FILE, DIP_ALL);
8401  filetype_indent = TRUE;
8402  }
8403  }
8404  if (*arg == 'd')
8405  {
8406  (void)do_doautocmd((char_u *)"filetypedetect BufRead", TRUE, NULL);
8407  do_modelines(0);
8408  }
8409  }
8410  else if (STRCMP(arg, "off") == 0)
8411  {
8412  if (plugin || indent)
8413  {
8414  if (plugin)
8415  {
8416  source_runtime((char_u *)FTPLUGOF_FILE, DIP_ALL);
8417  filetype_plugin = FALSE;
8418  }
8419  if (indent)
8420  {
8421  source_runtime((char_u *)INDOFF_FILE, DIP_ALL);
8422  filetype_indent = FALSE;
8423  }
8424  }
8425  else
8426  {
8427  source_runtime((char_u *)FTOFF_FILE, DIP_ALL);
8428  filetype_detect = FALSE;
8429  }
8430  }
8431  else
8432  semsg(_(e_invarg2), arg);
8433 }
